WEBVTT

00:22.272 --> 00:24.190
[PHONE RINGING]

00:26.443 --> 00:28.945
[THE PHARCYDE'S
"PASSING ME BY" PLAYING]

00:37.579 --> 00:39.872
SONNY: Hello?
MR. KOUFAX: Sonny, it's your dad.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.791
You asleep?
SONNY: No. Hey, man.

00:41.959 --> 00:43.876
I was exercising.

00:44.169 --> 00:46.629
Bullshit. You were sleeping.
No, I wasn't. I wasn't.

00:46.797 --> 00:50.258
This kid won't stop lying to me.
You still act like you're 6.

00:50.467 --> 00:53.803
SONNY:
Oh, yeah, okay, Dad. I act like I'm 6.

00:54.805 --> 00:57.807
MR. KOUFAX:
Any luck finding a job where you can
work more than one day a week?

00:58.058 --> 00:59.308
SONNY:
Uh, I've been looking.

01:00.018 --> 01:01.310
MR. KOUFAX:
Looking doesn't pay the rent, kid.

01:01.478 --> 01:03.938
SONNY:
Hey, all the money I won
from the cab accident

01:04.147 --> 01:06.607
is kicking ass
in the stock market, so relax.

01:06.817 --> 01:08.609
MR. KOUFAX:
Yeah, well, don't blow it
all on worthless crap.

01:08.777 --> 01:10.611
SONNY:
I won't.

01:11.113 --> 01:13.823
MR. KOUFAX:
You know what you should
spend it on? Your bar exam.

01:13.991 --> 01:16.617
SONNY:
You're the lawyer in the family.
I ain't taking a damn bar exam.

01:16.827 --> 01:18.828
I got too much other shit
going on in my life.

01:19.997 --> 01:21.706
MR. KOUFAX:
I don't know what the hell
happened to you.

01:21.874 --> 01:23.124
SONNY: Okay.
MR KOUFAX: Anyway.

01:23.292 --> 01:25.668
How are things going
with your girlfriend,
what's-her-name, Vanessa?

01:25.836 --> 01:27.044
Things are going fine.

01:27.212 --> 01:28.629
Shit!

01:28.797 --> 01:29.839
I gotta... I gotta go.

01:30.090 --> 01:32.842
Shit! You turned off
the alarm clock again.

01:33.010 --> 01:36.846
SONNY: No, no, no!
I mean, yes, I did, but I thought
you needed more sleep, Vanessa.

01:37.181 --> 01:38.306
I knew I shouldn't
have stayed here.

01:38.474 --> 01:40.600
That was a real jerk
thing to do. Thanks a lot.

01:40.851 --> 01:43.436
What are you doing? Why are
you going to work? It's Sunday.

01:43.687 --> 01:47.482
I'm not going to work.
I'm going to brunch with
some potential clients.

01:47.691 --> 01:51.319
That's how a party planner gets
business, by meeting people
and making contacts.

01:51.528 --> 01:54.864
Meet with me. Come on, I'll order
in from Cozy's. We'll have fun.

01:55.032 --> 01:58.868
I am sick of Cozy's. You order
in from there all the time.

01:59.036 --> 02:00.703
The delivery guy's
like your best friend.

02:00.871 --> 02:03.039
Well, he happens to be
pretty damn nice.

02:03.248 --> 02:05.124
This is a rough patch
in my life right now.

02:05.292 --> 02:08.794
Syracuse is 0 and 3.
And I got those
medical problems.

02:09.045 --> 02:10.170
Medical problems?

02:10.380 --> 02:14.133
A cab runs over your foot
two years ago. You spend
one night in the hospital.

02:14.301 --> 02:16.052
First of all, that cab was huge.

02:16.345 --> 02:20.515
And a jury decided that one night
of pain was worth $200,000.

02:20.724 --> 02:22.683
So there you go.
Whatever.

02:23.018 --> 02:25.394
What the hell's the matter?
Why are you being so nuts
to me lately?

02:25.562 --> 02:28.356
Because you refuse to move on
to the next phase of your life.

02:28.524 --> 02:30.483
I, on the other hand, would like
to have a family someday.

02:30.651 --> 02:33.361
But I need someone that I can
rely on, not just a playmate.

02:33.737 --> 02:36.906
What, you need a father figure?
"Stop pulling your sister's hair!"

02:37.533 --> 02:40.827
You know what? I'm gonna go
to Syracuse to see my mom.

02:41.912 --> 02:44.831
I'll be back on Wednesday.
What are you talking about?

02:47.918 --> 02:52.046
I had call for delivery in building,
but I think it was crank call.
You want some chocolate cake?

02:52.256 --> 02:54.799
It's a bad time, man.
Come back later.
I'll Indian wrestle you.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.342
You're going down,
sucker.

02:56.552 --> 02:57.593
Yeah, well,
we'll see about that.

02:57.803 --> 02:59.929
Okay. Peace, out.

03:00.389 --> 03:02.056
What do you mean
you're going to Syracuse?

03:02.266 --> 03:04.100
Because I need time to think
and so do you.

03:04.351 --> 03:05.434
What do I need to think about?

03:05.686 --> 03:08.354
Your life and why there's
any reason for me to be a part of it.

03:08.522 --> 03:10.273
All right.
While you're at it,

03:10.440 --> 03:12.942
why don't you think about
getting a real job?

03:13.110 --> 03:15.111
I got a real job!

03:15.320 --> 03:19.323
[EVERLAST & THE WHITE FOLX'S
"ONLY LOVE CAN BREAK YOUR
HEART" PLAYING]

03:21.702 --> 03:23.828
Patrick Ewing, nice shot.

03:24.621 --> 03:27.290
Hey, Sonny.
What's up, buddy boy?

03:27.457 --> 03:29.584
I'm out the door. Hey, pal.

03:30.627 --> 03:32.336
Where you going?
Manhattan.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.130
Manhattan?
You wanna take me with you?

03:34.339 --> 03:36.591
All right, I guess.

03:36.800 --> 03:38.634
All right, hold on to your money.
Later on, pal.

03:38.844 --> 03:40.344
Okay, take care, Sonny.

03:40.929 --> 03:41.971
See you.

03:42.598 --> 03:44.473
SONNY:
Cadillac, I love it.

04:04.661 --> 04:06.162
ALL:
Surprise!

04:06.371 --> 04:08.080
CORINNE:
Just ignore him.

04:08.248 --> 04:11.167
Shh, shh, shh.
It's only Sonny. It's only Sonny.

04:11.501 --> 04:13.878
Yeah, it's only me. It's only me.

04:14.546 --> 04:15.588
What's going on?

04:15.756 --> 04:17.714
Corinne's throwing a surprise
going-away party for Kevin.

04:17.882 --> 04:19.175
Why didn't she
tell me about it?

04:19.343 --> 04:20.676
The roommate has
a right to know.

04:20.928 --> 04:23.179
Because she knew you'd
tell him and ruin the surprise.

04:23.347 --> 04:24.388
No, I wouldn't.

04:27.017 --> 04:28.100
Hey, surprise.

04:28.518 --> 04:29.518
ALL:
Surprise.

04:29.853 --> 04:31.854
Surprise.
Surprise.

04:32.022 --> 04:33.105
What's going on?

04:37.194 --> 04:39.111
We wasted the good
surprise on you.

04:39.404 --> 04:40.529
All right.

04:43.075 --> 04:44.241
[DOOR SLAMS]

04:48.121 --> 04:49.205
Is this your handiwork?

04:49.456 --> 04:51.123
I guess.

04:51.541 --> 04:53.209
See you in three hours.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.962
Good to see you
stiffs out anyways.
What've you been doing?

04:56.171 --> 05:00.007
Last three weeks have been
crazy at work, man. I've been in
Denver, Dallas, San Francisco...

05:00.217 --> 05:01.425
I've been sleeping
in the office.

05:01.593 --> 05:03.886
We're going to trial on this
securities fraud case.

05:04.054 --> 05:07.056
Honey, it was a great surprise.
I was totally shocked.

05:07.224 --> 05:10.726
CORINNE: No, you weren't!
And I worked so hard on this.

05:10.936 --> 05:12.228
Need some help?

05:12.479 --> 05:14.897
Honey, your sister's here.
Hey, sweetie.

05:15.065 --> 05:17.066
CORINNE:
I hate Sonny.

05:17.234 --> 05:21.028
So my client's out 7 million bucks,
and all we can sue on is breach
of contract.

05:21.238 --> 05:24.573
Maybe you can try suing under
the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act.

05:25.158 --> 05:27.410
I gotta get back to the office.
Sonny, you're the king.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.745
Right on.
Mikey, a pleasure.

05:30.080 --> 05:32.081
I'll see you at home.
All right.

05:34.584 --> 05:36.669
I'll walk you out.
Okay.

05:38.046 --> 05:41.007
I gotta admit, I'm still a little
weirded out when they kiss.

05:41.216 --> 05:43.759
Why? They're gay.
That's what gay guys do.

05:43.969 --> 05:47.763
Yeah, I know, but they were like
brothers to us back in school.

05:47.973 --> 05:51.350
They're still like our brothers.
Our very, very gay brothers.

05:52.477 --> 05:55.521
What are you doing after this?
Going to a Klan meeting?

05:56.523 --> 05:58.399
Remember when Dad had
that huge barbecue

05:58.567 --> 06:00.359
for all his work friends
and then it rained,

06:00.569 --> 06:02.778
so he and Mom had to go into
the kitchen and make

06:02.988 --> 06:05.448
like a hundred hamburgers
with one frying pan?

06:05.615 --> 06:06.657
CORINNE:
Yeah.

06:06.825 --> 06:11.579
Well, you're not gonna let
a little rain stop you from making
a hundred hamburgers, are you?

06:12.122 --> 06:13.372
[LOCK CLICKS]

06:13.582 --> 06:16.584
[MELANIE C'S "GA GA" PLAYING]

06:20.630 --> 06:24.633
[THE CROWNSAYERS'
"DANCIN' IN THE MOONLIGHT"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

06:25.510 --> 06:28.220
That relationship's
lasted a lot longer
than I thought it would.

06:28.597 --> 06:31.766
Look at his eyes though.
He's bored out of his mind.
I give it two more weeks.

06:31.975 --> 06:34.268
Hey, excuse me.
Everybody! Hey!

06:34.436 --> 06:35.478
[MUSIC STOPS]

06:35.645 --> 06:37.980
I'm sorry. I wanted to thank you
all for coming tonight.

06:38.148 --> 06:39.607
Uh, or I guess I should say:

06:39.775 --> 06:41.150
[SPEAKS IN CHINESE]

06:42.986 --> 06:45.780
I'm getting it. Tomorrow
I'm leaving for China

06:45.947 --> 06:48.574
to represent the fine firm
of Morton and Mandel.

06:48.784 --> 06:51.869
Yes, me, the same guy who once
shaved his ass to win a $5 bet.

06:53.288 --> 06:54.830
Prove it!

06:57.042 --> 06:58.167
Just kidding.

06:58.543 --> 07:01.837
But I am real glad
you're all here tonight,

07:02.089 --> 07:05.007
because I'm about to do
something that I never thought
I'd have the guts to do.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.301
You're not proposing,
are you?

07:10.055 --> 07:12.181
Uh, yeah, pal, I am.

07:12.349 --> 07:14.475
Well, think about it,
you know?

07:14.684 --> 07:16.185
God, Sonny, shut up!

07:20.440 --> 07:23.526
Anyway, uh, will you?

07:24.486 --> 07:25.694
Yeah.

07:28.323 --> 07:30.074
Good call on the two weeks, pal.

07:35.580 --> 07:38.582
[RUFUS WAINWRIGHT'S
"INSTANT PLEASURE" PLAYING]

07:39.709 --> 07:41.460
Hey, Sonny,
what was that all about?

07:41.670 --> 07:45.005
Hey, congratulations.
You and Big Boobs McGee
are gonna be real happy.

07:45.215 --> 07:46.632
Don't call her Big Boobs McGee.

07:46.842 --> 07:51.095
You wanna explain to your children
you met their mother while she was
waitressing at Hooters?

07:51.388 --> 07:54.390
Sonny, that was five years ago.
She's a doctor now,

07:54.599 --> 07:56.684
and my fiancée,
so from now on,

07:56.893 --> 07:58.561
Dr. Big Boobs McGee.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.063
Congratulations.
Thanks, man.

08:01.231 --> 08:02.982
I just, uh,

08:03.733 --> 08:05.401
got shit going on.

08:05.652 --> 08:06.735
What's the matter?

08:06.987 --> 08:09.321
Vanessa's gonna
break up with me

08:09.531 --> 08:12.116
and I don't know what to do
to make her wanna stay.

08:12.325 --> 08:14.702
Vanessa's just getting older.
She wants different things,
you know?

08:14.911 --> 08:17.913
Career, stable relationship,
a family.

08:18.165 --> 08:19.331
That's how they get.

08:19.541 --> 08:22.501
I just want things to go back
to the way they used to be.

08:22.711 --> 08:24.003
Like when we were at Syracuse.
Yeah.

08:24.171 --> 08:25.337
And Vanessa worshiped you.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.547
Yes. That was nice.

08:26.715 --> 08:28.090
Nobody was hassling you
to get a job.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.134
Tommy and Phil were
showering separately.

08:31.595 --> 08:32.760
Those were the days.

08:33.638 --> 08:35.347
What are you doing?
If I make this putt,

08:35.515 --> 08:37.892
Vanessa will realize
she likes me the way I am.

08:38.101 --> 08:39.476
Oh, you're going to the putt.

08:39.811 --> 08:41.895
Remember, the roof
breaks to the right.

08:44.232 --> 08:46.233
Yes! That's what I'm talk...

08:46.401 --> 08:47.735
Good God!

08:47.944 --> 08:49.320
That can't be good.

08:54.659 --> 08:55.910
Where's Kevin?

08:56.203 --> 09:00.247
Oh, he already left. I guess
he forgot to say goodbye to you.

09:00.457 --> 09:01.916
Why are you here then?

09:02.083 --> 09:03.751
I'm cleaning
because you're useless.

09:03.919 --> 09:06.629
And then what, you gonna go
to your Hooters reunion?

09:06.838 --> 09:10.341
You guys can sit around,
talk about whose ass hangs
out of their shorts the most?

09:10.759 --> 09:13.219
At least I can fit my ass
into my shorts, fatty.

09:13.637 --> 09:15.304
Speaking of fatty,
whose is this?

09:15.513 --> 09:17.348
I don't know.
I'm eating it then.

09:17.515 --> 09:19.016
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

09:19.184 --> 09:21.518
"We wasted the good
surprise on you."

09:24.439 --> 09:25.481
Yeah?

09:25.649 --> 09:27.441
Lady gave me $5
to bring him over here.

09:27.651 --> 09:29.276
What do you mean?
Later.

09:30.237 --> 09:32.071
What, are you selling
raffle tickets or something?

09:39.162 --> 09:40.412
Oh, boy.

09:40.664 --> 09:42.248
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

09:43.166 --> 09:44.667
Kevin Gerrity.
SONNY: It's me.

09:44.834 --> 09:46.001
I got something to tell you.

09:46.169 --> 09:48.170
Yeah, what's up?
There's a kid here.

09:48.338 --> 09:49.421
Uh, what kind of kid?

09:49.673 --> 09:51.882
Uh, if this note is true,
it's your kid.

09:52.092 --> 09:53.342
What are you talking about?

09:54.261 --> 09:57.263
Um, I'm having a tough time
reading this,

09:57.472 --> 10:00.557
but I think it says, "Dear Kevin:
This is Julian, your son.

10:00.767 --> 10:03.477
I hope you understand why
I didn't tell you about him until now,

10:03.687 --> 10:07.356
but he needs your help.
I can't be his mother anymore."

10:07.565 --> 10:09.441
This is ridiculous.
Wait, hang on.

10:10.318 --> 10:11.694
Who's this?

10:12.195 --> 10:14.196
This is my friend.

10:14.614 --> 10:18.701
Is that Kevin on the phone?
No, it's my Uncle Remus.

10:20.328 --> 10:22.538
Hi. What's your name?

10:23.081 --> 10:24.123
Is he all right?

10:24.374 --> 10:26.250
Yeah, he just doesn't like you.
Leave us alone.

10:26.459 --> 10:27.876
You're such a dick.

10:28.086 --> 10:30.963
That was your girlfriend.
She was acting really
"Hooterific" again.

10:31.381 --> 10:33.966
Who sent that note?
"Jan."

10:34.217 --> 10:37.219
Jan... I don't know any Jan.

10:37.429 --> 10:39.388
Where's he from?
Where are you from, buddy?

10:39.556 --> 10:40.597
Buffalo.

10:40.849 --> 10:42.891
Buffalo. I've never
even been to Buffalo.

10:43.059 --> 10:44.768
Somebody's messing with me.
Maybe it's a mistake.

10:44.936 --> 10:47.938
Is there really a kid there?
Or is this like the time you
said my parents were dead?

10:48.106 --> 10:49.773
I swear to God, he's right here.

10:50.483 --> 10:53.235
I'm coming home, all right?
I don't know how I'm gonna
explain this to the partners...

10:53.445 --> 10:54.611
No, no, no. Hang on.

10:54.863 --> 10:59.074
It says here, "If you won't
take responsibility for him,
they found a foster family..."

10:59.284 --> 11:02.411
Yes, Uncle Remus,
I know the catfish are huge.

11:02.579 --> 11:03.787
That's terrific.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.165
Here's a number for a guy

11:06.416 --> 11:09.168
at City Social Service Bureau.
Arthur Brooks. I'll call him.

11:09.419 --> 11:11.462
I better come home.
No, no, no. Let me take care of it.

11:11.629 --> 11:14.006
You sure you can take care of this?
Yeah, I'll be fine, don't worry.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.301
Hooters. Hooters.
Hooters!

11:17.510 --> 11:19.678
All right, listen, Sonny. Thanks a lot.
Yeah, later.

11:22.766 --> 11:24.767
Well, I'm gonna make
another phone call.

11:25.185 --> 11:27.436
You want to come
and sit down, pal?

11:30.398 --> 11:33.567
Or you can stand there.
Anything you want.

11:33.735 --> 11:34.943
I'll be a minute.

11:35.445 --> 11:37.196
[RINGS]

11:37.405 --> 11:40.115
BROOKS [ON MESSAGE]:
Social Service office
is closed today, Columbus Day.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.701
We'll be open tomorrow
morning at 8 a.m.

11:43.203 --> 11:45.120
Columbus Day.

11:45.288 --> 11:46.872
[♪♪♪]

11:47.040 --> 11:49.041
Boy, I don't know
what to tell you, pal.

11:49.292 --> 11:51.710
Don't worry.
Everything's gonna get
figured out tomorrow.

11:51.920 --> 11:54.338
Can you be a tough
little guy until then?

11:55.298 --> 11:56.298
Great.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.385
Hey, do I need to get you a bottle
of formula or something?

11:59.552 --> 12:00.636
No.

12:00.804 --> 12:02.054
What do you eat?

12:02.222 --> 12:03.555
Food.

12:03.973 --> 12:05.974
Yeah? I eat food too.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.352
What? Come on.

12:08.520 --> 12:10.312
[♪♪♪]

12:11.523 --> 12:13.148
You need me
to hold your hand?

12:13.441 --> 12:14.817
What I like to do
on Monday afternoons

12:14.984 --> 12:17.403
is go to Central Park and watch
the rollerbladers fall down.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.738
You into that?
I don't know.

12:20.573 --> 12:21.824
SONNY:
Watch. This guy's humming.

12:21.991 --> 12:25.702
Ooh, ooh, ooh. He's going down,
he's going down, he's going!

12:26.037 --> 12:27.538
[GROANS]

12:28.081 --> 12:29.415
How old are you,
anyways?

12:29.582 --> 12:31.708
Five.
Five?

12:32.043 --> 12:33.585
You wear a diaper?

12:33.795 --> 12:35.254
No.

12:36.589 --> 12:38.507
You wipe your own ass then?
Yes.

12:38.716 --> 12:41.009
You do? Good job.
That's cool.

12:41.678 --> 12:44.847
Come on, fall down.
Fall down. Yes!
Oh, come on, damn it.

12:45.056 --> 12:46.723
You suck. You suck.
You suck!

12:47.892 --> 12:49.268
Check this out.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.937
[♪♪♪]

13:02.866 --> 13:04.032
SONNY:
My God!

13:04.242 --> 13:07.244
There's a stick there.
Somebody should move it.

13:07.579 --> 13:10.664
All right, now what way
would you put that on?

13:10.874 --> 13:13.375
This Columbo,
he pretends to be stupid,

13:13.626 --> 13:15.419
but he's really
smart as a tack.

13:15.628 --> 13:16.920
Oh, yeah,
he is.

13:17.130 --> 13:21.091
You put the vane on down there.
Then this boat comes up.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.385
I wipe my own ass.

13:24.220 --> 13:25.596
Me too.

13:28.057 --> 13:31.018
So, Mr. Ass Wiper,
what's this guy's name?

13:31.394 --> 13:32.853
Scuba Steve.

13:33.021 --> 13:35.189
I like his flippers.
Does he ever take them off?

13:35.398 --> 13:37.191
No.
How about if he goes bowling?

13:37.400 --> 13:40.068
They don't make him wear
bowling shoes? They let him
wear the flippers?

13:40.236 --> 13:41.653
Yes.
Really?

13:41.821 --> 13:43.947
I had a doll like that
at one time.

13:44.157 --> 13:46.783
But my cat,
he bite his head off.

13:46.993 --> 13:48.368
What kind of cat
would do that?

13:48.536 --> 13:49.620
You calling me a liar?

13:49.829 --> 13:51.538
Hey, take it easy.

13:52.957 --> 13:56.126
Anyways, Monday Night Football
is tonight. Jets are playing.

13:56.336 --> 13:59.129
We're gonna go to
the Blarney Stone, okay?
You wanna come with us?

13:59.464 --> 14:00.923
I've got more deliveries
on the bicycle.

14:01.090 --> 14:03.717
Well, maybe you can also
finish the turkey on your lip.

14:03.927 --> 14:05.177
Right there.

14:05.345 --> 14:06.512
[SONNY LAUGHS]

14:08.598 --> 14:10.224
[STYX'S "BLUE COLLAR MAN"
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

14:10.391 --> 14:11.892
SONNY:
Yeah, let's crank up the Styx.

14:12.101 --> 14:13.727
No music during the game.

14:13.937 --> 14:15.687
It's halftime.
Relax, Mr. Herlihy.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.147
Goddamn Jets.

14:17.398 --> 14:19.316
What are you doing
in here, cutie?

14:19.817 --> 14:21.443
Watching football.

14:21.653 --> 14:24.613
Who do you want to win?
The goddamn Jets.

14:25.823 --> 14:27.533
Have fun.

14:27.992 --> 14:29.826
[ELVIN BISHOP'S "FOOLED
AROUND AND FELL IN LOVE"
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

14:29.994 --> 14:32.788
Hey, too bad you don't like girls.
I think you could've had her.

14:33.039 --> 14:35.332
I'm thirsty.
You're thirsty?

14:35.583 --> 14:37.334
What do you want, a soda?
Are you allowed soda?

14:37.502 --> 14:38.544
I don't know.

14:38.711 --> 14:40.671
My mother always said
that soda rots your teeth,

14:40.838 --> 14:43.131
but you're gonna lose them
teeth anyway, so rot on, right?

14:43.675 --> 14:45.842
Can we get two root beers, please?
Sure.

14:46.844 --> 14:51.181
Man, when I graduated law school,
we used to meet here every Monday
night to watch football.

14:52.559 --> 14:53.976
Who would meet you?

14:54.602 --> 14:56.061
My friends, Vanessa.

14:56.604 --> 14:58.605
Vanessa always used
to root against the team

14:58.773 --> 15:00.816
I wanted to win
just to bust my chops.

15:01.067 --> 15:04.611
But everybody's so busy with their
crap lately, no one ever comes.

15:04.821 --> 15:06.655
Like I'm not busy?

15:06.990 --> 15:10.450
Hey, Mr. Herlihy, how about you
shut up or I'll smack you through
the wall like last Monday?

15:10.660 --> 15:13.829
Last Monday was a fluke.
Bring it on, woman.

15:14.497 --> 15:16.498
[LAUGHING]

15:17.500 --> 15:19.126
Anytime.

15:21.087 --> 15:22.504
He drinks a lot of soda.

15:27.176 --> 15:31.054
I'm telling you, buddy.
Vanessa, she's the one.
I can't lose her.

15:31.222 --> 15:33.056
I'm not getting any handsomer,
I know that.

15:33.224 --> 15:36.893
Every day I get a little bit older
and balder and fatter.

15:37.061 --> 15:38.770
Fatter?
Yeah.

15:38.938 --> 15:41.648
When I was your age,
I could eat anything I wanted.
Wouldn't gain an ounce.

15:41.858 --> 15:45.485
Now, I have a chocolate shake,
my ass jiggles for like a week.

15:45.695 --> 15:47.613
Enjoy the metabolism
while you got it.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.531
Metalobism?

15:50.908 --> 15:54.536
Good God, it's 2:30 in the morning.
You must be wrecked.

15:55.038 --> 15:58.540
Anyways, I had fun today.
Did you have fun?

15:59.250 --> 16:01.209
Yeah, you're all right.

16:02.128 --> 16:03.378
Have a good one.

16:04.464 --> 16:05.589
Sonny?

16:05.923 --> 16:07.049
Yes?

16:07.216 --> 16:09.217
Could I have a night-light?

16:09.427 --> 16:12.554
Night-light? I think I can
help you out. Hang on.

16:13.723 --> 16:15.724
[♪♪♪]

16:21.898 --> 16:22.898
Let's see here.

16:24.859 --> 16:26.735
There you go, all right?

16:27.403 --> 16:28.403
Sonny?

16:29.947 --> 16:31.448
Are you my dad?

16:31.949 --> 16:34.117
Oh, ah...

16:34.285 --> 16:36.119
No, I'm not,

16:36.287 --> 16:39.456
but that whole Dad and Mom thing
we'll figure out in the morning, okay?

16:41.584 --> 16:43.418
You just go to sleep.

16:45.088 --> 16:47.464
Good night.
Good night.

16:59.644 --> 17:02.437
[LIMP BIZKIT'S
"JUST LIKE THIS" PLAYING]

17:02.689 --> 17:04.439
Go get the can,
okay?

17:04.607 --> 17:06.692
Go! Go! Go!

17:09.820 --> 17:11.988
I'm thinking about
keeping the kid.

17:13.616 --> 17:17.202
Sonny. Remember that time
you went with me to the
pet store to get fish food

17:17.369 --> 17:21.498
and you saw that cute little puppy
and you wanted to get it, but then
I reminded you about feeding it

17:21.665 --> 17:22.874
and cleaning it
and toilet training it?

17:23.041 --> 17:24.917
Yeah.
Well, this is kind of like that,

17:25.086 --> 17:26.920
except with a human.

17:27.130 --> 17:30.507
I mean, I'm glad you had
fun and all, but this is big.

17:30.717 --> 17:34.136
I gotta do something big with my life.
I think Vanessa will respect that.

17:34.303 --> 17:38.807
So you're thinking that since
sometimes women get pregnant
to try to fix a troubled relationship,

17:39.016 --> 17:41.518
why can't a guy adopt a kid
to do the same thing?

17:41.728 --> 17:45.355
I didn't think of it like that.
But, yeah, that's a good point.
Yes, that's what I'm thinking.

17:45.648 --> 17:46.815
Sounds nuts
to me, pal.

17:46.983 --> 17:49.025
Do yourself a favor.
Sleep on it.

17:49.277 --> 17:51.111
You're right. Can I borrow
your cell phone for a minute?

17:52.530 --> 17:54.156
Thank you.

17:55.241 --> 17:56.283
[PHONE RINGS]

17:57.493 --> 17:59.035
Hello. Arthur Brooks speaking.

17:59.203 --> 18:00.996
Hey, Mr. Brooks, how you doing?
Kevin Gerrity here.

18:01.164 --> 18:02.664
Ah, right on, Mr. Gerrity.

18:02.832 --> 18:04.166
We were expecting your call.

18:04.333 --> 18:07.627
Yeah, I was wondering,
do you still got a foster family
lined up for Julian?

18:07.795 --> 18:08.837
Yes, we do.

18:09.005 --> 18:11.882
Well, you can cancel them.
I've decided to take care
of the little guy.

18:12.049 --> 18:13.383
Way to sleep
on it, pal.

18:13.551 --> 18:16.845
Hey, you two want to get
married, I support that.
Leave me alone.

18:17.013 --> 18:21.183
When natural parents take
the responsibility, I mean, there's
absolutely no bigger high for us.

18:21.350 --> 18:22.851
I'm psyched about it too, buddy.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.060
So I guess that's it.

18:24.270 --> 18:26.271
Yep, that's it. And good luck
to you and your son.

18:27.482 --> 18:28.774
My son.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.404
MAN:
Goddamn stick!

18:34.572 --> 18:36.072
That's my boy.

18:47.043 --> 18:49.419
Hey.
Hi.

18:50.296 --> 18:51.588
Go back to sleep, all right?

18:53.883 --> 18:57.427
Well, I'm going back to sleep.
Nighty-night.

18:58.054 --> 18:59.596
I wet my bed.

19:04.894 --> 19:06.478
Oh?

19:06.813 --> 19:10.065
[EURYTHMICS' "SWEET DREAMS
(ARE MADE OF THIS)" PLAYING]

19:17.448 --> 19:19.366
Oh, God.

19:19.742 --> 19:22.118
That's a shitload of piss.

19:24.997 --> 19:26.623
Okay.

19:36.843 --> 19:38.593
There you go,
all right?

19:38.845 --> 19:40.637
No more wet mess.

19:41.430 --> 19:45.100
Sleep, all right?
Just try to sleep. Stay asleep.

19:54.402 --> 19:56.403
[NEWSPAPER RUSTLING]

20:03.619 --> 20:05.620
[RUSTLING CONTINUES]

20:12.295 --> 20:13.962
No.

20:17.008 --> 20:18.884
Sit still!

20:19.468 --> 20:20.510
Lay!

20:28.311 --> 20:29.769
All right! I'm up!

20:29.979 --> 20:33.481
It smells like urine
in this joint. Good job.

20:34.483 --> 20:36.151
What are you
doing there, boy?

20:36.402 --> 20:37.694
Making cereal.

20:37.904 --> 20:40.697
Oh, yeah? Why don't you
pour me a bowl?

20:45.828 --> 20:47.829
Or don't pour me a bowl.
Either way.

20:47.997 --> 20:49.497
I got it. I got it. I got it.

20:49.665 --> 20:51.333
[CRYING]

20:51.500 --> 20:53.835
Hey, hey, hey.
We can fix this.

20:54.045 --> 20:55.378
Hey.

20:55.546 --> 20:57.547
It's not a big deal.

20:57.798 --> 20:59.424
Look. See?

20:59.634 --> 21:01.843
See how quick it goes away?

21:02.720 --> 21:04.054
Crybaby, come on.

21:04.513 --> 21:06.056
Don't worry about it, boy.

21:06.349 --> 21:08.308
Ow!

21:08.726 --> 21:10.936
Scuba Steve,
damn you!

21:12.146 --> 21:14.648
You like that? You think
that's funny, me getting hurt?

21:15.858 --> 21:17.692
Ha, ha.

21:19.236 --> 21:23.031
There's a bright side to
being up before 11: We can
catch McDonald's breakfast.

21:23.199 --> 21:26.076
I haven't been up in time
for that in like 10 years.
You wanna do that?

21:27.453 --> 21:29.329
Tie your shoes, we'll go.
Hurry though.

21:30.456 --> 21:33.375
It's like 12 blocks
from here, so tie quickly.

21:34.043 --> 21:36.044
[♪♪♪]

21:37.713 --> 21:39.464
Do you need help with that?

21:39.674 --> 21:41.257
I can do it.

21:43.052 --> 21:44.386
Let me do it.

21:44.553 --> 21:46.888
[♪♪♪]

21:47.056 --> 21:50.976
All right. You loop it,
you swoop it, and you pull.

21:51.185 --> 21:54.270
You loop it,
you swoop it, you pull.

21:54.522 --> 21:56.481
Good, good. All right, let's go.
We're in a hurry.

21:56.774 --> 21:58.400
SONNY:
See, it's different
for your generation.

21:58.567 --> 22:01.736
You guys have always had
the McDonald's breakfast
available to you.

22:01.904 --> 22:02.946
JULIAN:
I have?

22:03.114 --> 22:06.241
SONNY: Yeah, yeah.
When I was born, all we had
were the burgers and fries.

22:06.409 --> 22:07.450
Maybe the fish sandwich.

22:07.618 --> 22:09.911
I'm not sure. I gotta
get back to you on that.

22:10.121 --> 22:11.413
What are you doing?

22:11.998 --> 22:13.915
Oh, yeah, the hand-holding thing.

22:15.084 --> 22:18.920
I remember my dad took us
to McDonald's the very first
morning they had breakfast.

22:19.130 --> 22:20.422
Everybody was baffled
in the place.

22:20.589 --> 22:22.632
They were like,
"Are these sausages or
are these hamburgers?"

22:22.800 --> 22:24.592
I have to go
to the bathroom.

22:24.760 --> 22:26.928
You what? We're gonna
be there in a minute.

22:27.138 --> 22:28.638
I gotta go now.

22:28.806 --> 22:30.515
Hey, didn't you pee enough
in bed already?

22:31.600 --> 22:34.519
We only got nine minutes
to get there.

22:34.729 --> 22:37.772
But I gotta go to the bathroom.

22:38.024 --> 22:39.441
All right, let's go.

22:40.443 --> 22:42.569
Hey, buddy, can my kid use
the bathroom for a minute?

22:42.737 --> 22:43.778
Customers only.

22:43.946 --> 22:46.114
Oh, yeah, he's just a kid.
Come on, we'll be in and out.

22:46.282 --> 22:47.741
It's not my problem.

22:47.908 --> 22:50.452
It's not your problem?
All right.

22:50.745 --> 22:51.828
Come on.

22:51.996 --> 22:53.788
[♪♪♪]

22:54.331 --> 22:57.542
Here you are. Your waiter
will be right with you.

22:59.045 --> 23:00.420
I can't do it.

23:00.588 --> 23:03.048
What do you mean, you can't do it?
You said you gotta go. Just go.

23:03.215 --> 23:06.551
I'm scared.
Could you do it too?

23:08.471 --> 23:09.637
All right.

23:12.558 --> 23:13.850
Here we go.

23:14.643 --> 23:16.102
And we're off.

23:18.272 --> 23:20.690
That's not too difficult, right?

23:21.067 --> 23:23.485
And we're both
losing weight.

23:23.986 --> 23:27.113
Good job. All right,
we're gonna miss
breakfast. Let's go.

23:27.323 --> 23:30.158
Put it away. Yeah.

23:31.368 --> 23:35.497
Hey. Thanks, anyways.
Sure thing. Anytime.

23:35.664 --> 23:37.332
SONNY: Come on.
Move your ass there, pee-boy.

23:37.583 --> 23:40.877
We only got five minutes,
five minutes. Now four.

23:41.087 --> 23:43.338
Come on. We're almost there.
We're almost there.

23:43.672 --> 23:46.508
Hey, mister. Why are you
sitting on the ground?

23:46.967 --> 23:48.176
This is where I live, little man.

23:48.344 --> 23:50.428
We gotta get going, pal.
Why?

23:50.846 --> 23:54.224
Well, in retrospect,
I made some really bad
choices after high school.

23:54.391 --> 23:56.309
Yeah. We gotta get going, buddy.
Why?

23:56.519 --> 23:59.020
Well, this was during
the so-called Disco Era,

23:59.188 --> 24:02.732
but for me, it was more
the Doing Mushrooms Era.

24:02.900 --> 24:05.360
Okay. We're gonna miss breakfast.
Why?

24:05.528 --> 24:06.861
I never really thought
about that, kid.

24:07.029 --> 24:09.614
I mean, I was never
Mr. Popularity in high school,

24:09.824 --> 24:12.367
and I watched Fantasia a lot.

24:12.618 --> 24:14.202
And one day it just clicked.
SONNY: Hey, yappy.

24:14.411 --> 24:16.704
If you end the conversation,
I'll get you an Egg McMuffin.

24:16.914 --> 24:19.040
How about a Sausage McMuffin
with hash browns?

24:19.208 --> 24:20.542
You got a deal.

24:22.128 --> 24:24.754
Look, look, look. He fell asleep.
He fell asleep. Let's go.

24:25.506 --> 24:26.548
Let's go.

24:26.715 --> 24:28.716
[♪♪♪]

24:30.427 --> 24:33.054
Sausage McMuffin.

24:33.264 --> 24:34.597
Pardon me, sir. Sorry.

24:34.765 --> 24:36.057
Hey. How you doing?

24:36.225 --> 24:37.767
Welcome to McDonald's.
What can I get for you?

24:37.935 --> 24:39.894
Okay, what do you want?
Cheerios.

24:40.062 --> 24:41.729
Cheerios. They don't got
Cheerios. What else?

24:42.565 --> 24:43.606
Lasagna.

24:43.774 --> 24:45.233
Lasagna? What the hell's
the matter with you?

24:45.401 --> 24:46.776
We'll take hotcakes
and sausage.

24:47.027 --> 24:49.070
Sorry, sir. We stopped
serving breakfast.

24:49.280 --> 24:51.239
What are you talking about?
We're four seconds late.

24:51.448 --> 24:54.576
No, you're 30 minutes and four
seconds late. We stop serving
breakfast at 10:30.

24:54.743 --> 24:56.161
Ah, horseshit!

24:56.328 --> 24:58.329
[JULIAN CRYING]

24:59.123 --> 25:00.790
No, no, no. Don't cry.
I'm sorry.

25:01.041 --> 25:02.917
I wasn't cursing at you,
I was cursing at the lady.

25:03.127 --> 25:04.169
Nice parenting.

25:04.336 --> 25:06.921
Hey, thanks. Are you my
therapist? Take a walk.

25:07.089 --> 25:08.756
Do you want a Happy Meal?
We'll get you one.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.633
You got a Happy Meal?
Can we get a Happy Meal?

25:10.801 --> 25:12.760
Will somebody get
the kid a Happy Meal?!

25:13.304 --> 25:14.429
Relax.

25:14.680 --> 25:15.972
Hey, where's my
Egg McMuffin?

25:16.223 --> 25:17.974
Breakfast is over
at 10:30.

25:18.142 --> 25:19.184
Really?
Yeah.

25:19.351 --> 25:21.269
I thought it was 11.
I thought that too.

25:22.771 --> 25:24.564
Total mind blower.

25:24.773 --> 25:26.858
Will you just relax? Here.

25:27.026 --> 25:28.943
What do you want me to do?
What would cheer you up?

25:29.111 --> 25:32.322
You're gonna meet Vanessa tonight.
She's nice. You'll like her.

25:32.698 --> 25:35.283
You wanna see me get hurt?
Will that cheer you up some?

25:36.118 --> 25:37.202
All right.

25:38.454 --> 25:40.079
[CAR HORN HONKS]

25:42.833 --> 25:44.709
You like that, huh?
You think that's funny?

25:46.003 --> 25:47.420
Good. No more crying.

25:47.588 --> 25:48.630
Are you okay, man?

25:48.964 --> 25:50.798
Next time, kill me.

25:50.966 --> 25:53.968
["ONLY LOVE CAN BREAK
YOUR HEART" PLAYING]

26:06.982 --> 26:08.024
Let's do it, Rangers.

26:08.275 --> 26:10.777
ANNOUNCER [ON TV]:
- New York Rangers against
the Tampa Bay Lightning.

26:10.986 --> 26:12.320
And at this stage
of the season,

26:12.529 --> 26:16.366
it's as close as you can get
to a must-win game for the Rangers.

26:16.533 --> 26:18.159
Otherwise they'll fall behind...

26:18.369 --> 26:20.328
How you doing?
How you doing?

26:21.038 --> 26:23.248
You like hockey?
You like hockey?

26:23.749 --> 26:27.252
This is a big, important game.

26:27.670 --> 26:30.046
Cut the crap.
Cut the crap.

26:31.674 --> 26:35.009
I'm being serious.
Don't do that.

26:35.177 --> 26:36.678
How much wood
would a woodchuck chuck

26:36.845 --> 26:39.722
if a woodchuck
could chuck wood?

26:39.890 --> 26:41.516
Yeah, that's what I thought.
Shut up.

26:43.394 --> 26:44.769
Hey, don't you take naps?

26:44.979 --> 26:46.062
Sometimes.

26:46.272 --> 26:47.522
Well, why don't you
go take a nap?

26:47.773 --> 26:49.691
I'm too hungry to sleep.

26:50.526 --> 26:52.277
You want some food?

27:05.291 --> 27:07.375
[WHISPERS]
Having a kid is great,

27:07.710 --> 27:12.005
as long as his eyes are closed
and he's not moving or speaking.

27:12.214 --> 27:14.424
[ANNOUNCER
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

27:34.570 --> 27:36.404
ANNOUNCER:
He's taken down! Penalty shot!

27:36.780 --> 27:37.989
[GRUNTS]

27:41.368 --> 27:43.953
Hey, how you doing there, boy?
You sleepwalking? Huh?

27:44.705 --> 27:46.914
Why don't you go
back sleepy? Sleepy.

27:47.124 --> 27:48.666
Keep napping. What's this?

27:48.834 --> 27:49.917
Kangaroo song.

27:50.085 --> 27:53.755
All right, great. That's terrific.
And we're gonna watch this
after the game, okay?

27:53.922 --> 27:57.300
But after my nap, I always
watch the kangaroo song.

27:57.760 --> 28:01.512
It's overtime right now, and there's
a penalty shot about to take place.

28:01.680 --> 28:02.847
This happens like
once every 10 years...

28:03.015 --> 28:05.099
Kangaroo song. Kangaroo song!

28:05.267 --> 28:07.935
Kangaroo song! Kangaroo song!

28:08.145 --> 28:10.730
All right!

28:11.732 --> 28:13.858
God! You were
normal yesterday.

28:14.943 --> 28:17.945
["THE KANGAROO SONG"
PLAYING ON TV]

28:18.280 --> 28:19.947
KANGAROO [SINGING]:

28:25.871 --> 28:27.663
I can't take this shit.
Are you serious?

28:27.915 --> 28:29.374
KANGAROO [SINGING]:
Come and play

28:29.541 --> 28:31.542
KANGAROO & KIDS [SINGING]:

28:31.794 --> 28:33.586
What do you say?

28:33.796 --> 28:35.171
Douche-bag kangaroo.

28:38.801 --> 28:40.426
What happened there?
Are you all hopped out?

28:44.181 --> 28:46.682
All right, I don't know how
to deal with this. Hopefully
Vanessa will.

28:46.892 --> 28:49.394
I think she's back.
If she's not back,
we'll wait for her.

28:49.561 --> 28:52.021
Jeez. Come on,
get your coat. Clean up.

28:53.690 --> 28:56.401
Oh, God. You don't
have to pee, do you?

28:56.568 --> 28:58.236
No.
Do you swear?

28:58.404 --> 28:59.445
I swear.

28:59.613 --> 29:01.155
[♪♪♪]

29:01.323 --> 29:02.657
How come
you're not going?

29:02.825 --> 29:06.619
Because I don't have to go.
Only you and my grandfather
go every 30 seconds.

29:06.829 --> 29:09.330
Let's hurry it up, all right?
I'm keeping you company.

29:09.498 --> 29:10.498
Hi!

29:11.667 --> 29:14.669
What's your name? He'll write it
on the wall. Mind your business.

29:16.296 --> 29:18.423
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

29:19.049 --> 29:21.050
Why do I need to meet this lady?

29:21.218 --> 29:23.970
Hey, now it is your problem.
Oh, thank you. Thank you.

29:24.179 --> 29:26.139
This is that lady I was
telling you about.

29:26.348 --> 29:28.933
She's gonna be a big part
of your life from now on.

29:29.184 --> 29:32.061
I'm scared.
What if she's not nice?

29:32.229 --> 29:33.646
Look.

29:34.189 --> 29:37.608
See these right here? These are
magic sunglasses, okay?

29:37.943 --> 29:40.194
If you're afraid, you put them on,
they make you invisible.

29:40.446 --> 29:42.196
Really? Nobody can see me?

29:42.364 --> 29:43.698
Put them on.

29:44.908 --> 29:47.660
Julian? Julian!
Hello, Julian?

29:47.828 --> 29:49.203
Hey, Sonny,
I'm right here.

29:49.371 --> 29:51.456
Oh, the glasses.
I couldn't see you.

29:51.665 --> 29:55.293
Now, you keep those on
and no one can notice you
until you decide they can, okay?

29:55.586 --> 29:56.878
Okay.
All right, let's go.

29:57.045 --> 29:58.754
[♪♪♪]

29:58.922 --> 30:01.632
Julian? Julian?
I'm still right here.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.260
Oh, okay, all right,
the glasses.

30:05.137 --> 30:06.179
[DOORBELL RINGS]

30:07.222 --> 30:09.015
SONNY: Hey.
Hi.

30:09.224 --> 30:10.266
Welcome back.

30:10.434 --> 30:12.393
Who's that?
Who's who?

30:12.561 --> 30:13.895
[WHISPERS]
He's invisible.

30:15.481 --> 30:16.606
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Can I come in?

30:16.899 --> 30:18.232
Sure.

30:18.901 --> 30:20.818
Hey, any invisible people
out here,

30:20.986 --> 30:23.112
feel free to come in, okay?

30:25.741 --> 30:29.785
Sonny, I don't really know
what's going on right now,
but we should sit down and talk...

30:29.953 --> 30:31.829
You know you said
I got some thinking to do?

30:31.997 --> 30:33.289
So I did it.

30:33.457 --> 30:37.293
Just because I don't have a job
doesn't mean I don't wanna
move on to the next level.

30:37.461 --> 30:39.837
And instead of just saying
that to you, I figured
I would show you.

30:40.005 --> 30:41.756
Before you say anything else,
I just want you to know...

30:41.924 --> 30:44.133
Look at that. He took
his sunglasses off.

30:44.301 --> 30:46.552
He wants you to see him.
That means he likes you.

30:47.095 --> 30:48.137
Julian, come here.

30:49.431 --> 30:50.932
Come here, pal.

30:51.225 --> 30:52.600
Vanessa,

30:52.768 --> 30:55.645
I want you to meet
Julian, my son.

30:56.772 --> 30:58.314
Our son. I adopted him.

30:59.775 --> 31:01.609
I don't know what to say.

31:01.818 --> 31:03.152
You don't have to
say anything.

31:03.320 --> 31:04.362
[CLATTERING]

31:04.530 --> 31:05.655
Uh... Heh-heh.

31:06.782 --> 31:08.115
Is somebody in the bathroom?

31:09.243 --> 31:10.284
No.

31:10.452 --> 31:11.452
Why is the door shut?

31:11.620 --> 31:12.662
I don't know.

31:12.829 --> 31:14.789
You don't?
Mm-mm.

31:15.749 --> 31:18.501
I don't know.
VANESSA: Sonny.

31:20.837 --> 31:22.171
I can't believe this.

31:23.131 --> 31:25.007
Hey. Open up.

31:25.175 --> 31:26.217
Sonny.

31:26.385 --> 31:28.469
Hello. Open the door!

31:28.637 --> 31:30.096
VANESSA:
Sonny.

31:30.305 --> 31:33.558
Is everything okay?
Oh, my God.

31:34.059 --> 31:36.060
Man, I'm sorry.
I was freaking out there.

31:36.270 --> 31:37.853
I'm Sonny.
Sid.

31:38.105 --> 31:42.066
Hey, Sid. I had an attack
of paranoia. I thought you
were sleeping with my girl.

31:42.276 --> 31:43.651
I am.

31:43.860 --> 31:45.611
What's that?

31:46.196 --> 31:47.321
I am.

31:47.573 --> 31:50.992
Sonny, that's what I was
trying to tell you before.
I found someone.

31:51.201 --> 31:53.160
This old guy?
Sid.

31:53.328 --> 31:55.162
He's already achieved
so much,

31:55.372 --> 31:58.332
and yet he's still goal-oriented
and still focused.

31:58.584 --> 32:00.084
And he has
a five-year plan.

32:00.294 --> 32:01.794
What is it? "Don't die"?

32:02.671 --> 32:04.547
I can't believe this shit.
We got a family now.

32:04.715 --> 32:06.841
I thought this is what
you wanted.

32:07.009 --> 32:10.845
Sonny, you surprising me with a kid
that you adopted while I was away
wasn't what I said I wanted.

32:11.013 --> 32:12.346
SONNY:
I did this for you.

32:12.598 --> 32:14.807
You wanted me
to be more responsible.

32:14.975 --> 32:16.475
I can't raise this kid alone.

32:16.685 --> 32:20.021
You know, you remind me
of my oldest grandson.
You don't think things through.

32:20.230 --> 32:23.107
Hey, Old Man River,
zip it or I'll break your hip.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.401
I'd like to see you try it.
Shut up, Sid.

32:25.611 --> 32:28.195
How could you misconstrue
the situation so badly?

32:28.405 --> 32:30.114
I don't know.

32:31.033 --> 32:32.533
Come on.
Deep down you must've known

32:32.701 --> 32:33.909
this day was gonna come.

32:34.119 --> 32:37.663
Hey. You just made the biggest
mistake of your life, baby.

32:37.873 --> 32:40.041
I know you're gonna be
missing me when you got

32:40.250 --> 32:42.585
that big, white, wrinkly

32:42.753 --> 32:44.337
body on top of you,

32:44.546 --> 32:46.380
with his loose skin

32:46.632 --> 32:48.424
and old balls.

32:48.634 --> 32:50.259
Gross. Ugh.

32:50.636 --> 32:52.887
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

32:53.055 --> 32:54.889
[♪♪♪]

32:55.849 --> 32:57.767
[JULIAN SINGING]

32:57.934 --> 33:01.187
Excuse me. How you doing?
I'm Kevin Gerrity.

33:01.396 --> 33:04.190
Hey, I got an emergency
problem with this kid here.
Is Arthur Brooks around?

33:04.399 --> 33:05.650
Yeah, I'll go get him for you.

33:05.817 --> 33:09.403
Can you sit over there for a while?
Stay where I can see you.
I gotta talk to this guy.

33:09.571 --> 33:10.946
Mr. Gerrity?

33:11.365 --> 33:13.074
Hi. Arthur Brooks.
How are you?

33:13.241 --> 33:14.575
I need to speak with you.

33:14.785 --> 33:16.869
I didn't tell you to come down
to the office, did I?

33:17.079 --> 33:19.413
Because I was
gonna send you the final
paperwork in the mail, man.

33:19.581 --> 33:21.415
It's like the opposite of that.

33:21.583 --> 33:23.668
Look, I can't manage
this kid.

33:23.960 --> 33:26.921
I ain't a good father.
I made a big mistake.

33:27.089 --> 33:29.674
Mistake?
I had a mother lined up for him,

33:29.841 --> 33:33.469
but she's banging
the Pepperidge Farm guy.

33:33.679 --> 33:35.930
The kid just won't stop
peeing and throwing up.

33:36.098 --> 33:38.808
He's like a cocker spaniel.
I just...

33:39.059 --> 33:41.310
I think he'd be better off
with his natural mother.

33:42.104 --> 33:44.939
Well, she passed away
last night, Mr. Gerrity.

33:45.107 --> 33:49.443
She had cancer. She must
have sensed that, like,
her time was running short

33:49.611 --> 33:52.446
and that she wanted her son
to be with the natural father.
It makes sense.

33:55.409 --> 33:56.701
Loop.

33:57.285 --> 33:58.327
Pull.

33:59.287 --> 34:00.996
Look, if you don't wanna
take care of Julian,

34:01.164 --> 34:04.834
we'll take him. But I gotta tell you,
man, he's gonna have to chill
for a while in a group home.

34:05.001 --> 34:06.794
Group home? What is that,
like an orphanage?

34:06.962 --> 34:08.462
Yeah. We don't call
them that anymore.

34:08.630 --> 34:09.839
JULIAN:
Hey, hey!

34:10.005 --> 34:11.172
[♪♪♪]

34:11.341 --> 34:14.301
Look, I did it.
Loop, swoop and pull.

34:14.469 --> 34:15.511
Jeez, you did do it.

34:15.721 --> 34:17.138
Congratulations, kid.

34:17.304 --> 34:18.973
I showed him that.

34:19.141 --> 34:21.600
Why don't you
go back over there, okay?

34:22.351 --> 34:23.643
BROOKS:
I'll call the Heatherton Home...

34:23.812 --> 34:25.146
No, why don't we do this?

34:25.313 --> 34:28.774
Temporarily I'll hang on to the kid
until you find him a new family.

34:28.984 --> 34:32.319
Oh, I don't know, man.
I mean, I gotta watch out for
the best interest of the kid.

34:32.529 --> 34:34.822
You said yourself you
were a bogus dad.

34:34.989 --> 34:37.199
He's better off with me
than in an orphanage.

34:37.367 --> 34:40.202
I don't wanna put him in a home
any more than you do.

34:40.370 --> 34:43.246
Why don't we pretend that you didn't
even come in here today, okay?

34:43.456 --> 34:46.375
And I'll give you a shout
when I line up a family, all right?

34:46.543 --> 34:47.835
That's good. Okay.
Later.

34:48.043 --> 34:49.879
Just don't make me regret this.

34:50.630 --> 34:52.130
Where are we
going now?

34:52.340 --> 34:56.510
I gotta make a phone call.
Just stay right here, all right?

34:57.179 --> 34:59.472
[PHONE RINGS]

35:00.724 --> 35:01.766
Hello?

35:01.933 --> 35:03.434
OPERATOR:
This is a collect call from:

35:03.602 --> 35:04.643
SONNY:
Your baby boy.

35:04.811 --> 35:06.437
OPERATOR:
To accept charges, say, "Yes."

35:06.605 --> 35:07.688
Yeah, I'll accept.

35:07.856 --> 35:09.857
Hey, Dad, how's it going?
How's Florida?

35:10.192 --> 35:13.569
Not too bad.
Your mother got a sunburn
playing tennis yesterday.

35:13.737 --> 35:15.237
I got some
interesting news.

35:15.405 --> 35:16.822
Oh, yeah? What?

35:17.032 --> 35:18.741
Kind of adopted a kid.

35:18.909 --> 35:20.075
What the hell
are you talking about?

35:20.327 --> 35:23.245
I'm talking about you being
a grandfather. Congratulations.

35:23.413 --> 35:25.289
Who the hell would give you a kid?

35:25.499 --> 35:26.916
Social Services.

35:27.083 --> 35:29.502
You idiot. You better give
that kid back.

35:29.711 --> 35:31.337
His mother's...

35:31.588 --> 35:32.797
Hang on. Hang on.

35:33.006 --> 35:35.007
Go play with them
pigeons, buddy.

35:35.342 --> 35:38.427
I tried to give him back.
I just can't, Dad. All right?

35:38.678 --> 35:40.054
Look, I need your help.

35:40.222 --> 35:42.515
I'm in a bad way right now.
Vanessa dumped me.

35:42.682 --> 35:44.016
I don't know what the hell
I'm doing.

35:44.226 --> 35:45.935
You're damn right you don't know
what the hell you're doing.

35:46.102 --> 35:48.020
The kid is always around.

35:48.230 --> 35:50.397
The past three days,
he just never leaves me alone.

35:50.565 --> 35:53.859
You would think he'd want
some privacy, but he doesn't.
I'm in deep shit.

35:54.069 --> 35:56.821
Just give that kid back
before you ruin both your lives.

35:56.988 --> 35:58.322
Oh, I appreciate that, Dad.

35:58.532 --> 36:00.616
He'd be better off living in
a dumpster than living with you.

36:00.867 --> 36:02.576
I'll be a better father than you!

36:02.744 --> 36:05.079
That's impossible! Because
all you care about is yourself!

36:05.247 --> 36:08.707
Yeah? No, I care about you
saving money on this phone call!

36:14.089 --> 36:15.422
Let's eat.

36:15.590 --> 36:16.841
[♪♪♪]

36:17.008 --> 36:18.968
SONNY:
The Vanessa thing did not work out.

36:19.219 --> 36:22.096
She lost her damn mind.
That wasn't your fault,
though, okay?

36:22.264 --> 36:23.931
JULIAN:
Okay.

36:24.558 --> 36:28.602
I know when you first got here
you thought you were gonna
meet your dad, but, pal,

36:28.770 --> 36:31.146
I gotta tell you, I don't think
that's gonna happen.

36:31.398 --> 36:33.774
Why?
I don't know why.

36:34.234 --> 36:36.944
But, buddy, real dads aren't
always that great, you know.

36:37.153 --> 36:39.113
I got a real dad
and the guy's out of his mind.

36:39.281 --> 36:43.158
He's been telling me what to do
my whole life. He never lets me
figure stuff out on my own.

36:43.368 --> 36:46.620
A lot of dads are like that.
That's why so many people
grow up nuts.

36:47.455 --> 36:48.873
Look at this guy
over here.

36:49.040 --> 36:50.499
He was probably
a nice boy just like you.

36:50.667 --> 36:52.960
Then his dad messed his mind up.
Now look at him.

36:53.128 --> 36:54.628
Hey, buddy.
Who won the Jets game?

36:54.796 --> 36:55.838
Who cares?

36:56.006 --> 36:58.299
Let it go, pal. He can't
control you anymore.

36:58.466 --> 36:59.508
What are you talking about?

36:59.759 --> 37:02.052
You know what I'm talking about.
Yeah, you're a loser.

37:02.304 --> 37:04.889
You're mad at your dad,
not at me! I forgive you!

37:05.390 --> 37:08.017
I am. I am.
I hate my father.

37:08.393 --> 37:12.021
See, I don't want it to be like that.
I don't wanna control you, Julian.

37:12.188 --> 37:13.731
You even like that name,
Julian?

37:13.899 --> 37:15.316
I guess.

37:15.525 --> 37:17.651
You guess? Well, shouldn't
you like your own name?

37:17.819 --> 37:20.529
Why don't you pick your name?
It's gonna be your name
the rest of your life.

37:20.697 --> 37:21.947
What do you want it to be?

37:24.034 --> 37:25.618
Frankenstein.

37:25.827 --> 37:29.038
Frankenstein? All right.
I can deal with that.
I'll call you Frankenstein.

37:29.289 --> 37:31.332
What are you doing, Frankenstein?
You gonna play in the puddle?

37:31.499 --> 37:34.793
Well, go ahead. Puddle it up.
From now on, you do
whatever you wanna do.

37:35.003 --> 37:37.338
And I'll show you some
cool shit along the way.

37:37.505 --> 37:39.048
That's what it's all about.

37:39.215 --> 37:41.050
[GARBAGE'S "WHEN I GROW UP"
PLAYING]

37:41.217 --> 37:43.177
SONNY:
Stay in front of it.
Don't be scared.

37:43.345 --> 37:45.220
Here we go.
It's coming right at you.

37:45.722 --> 37:46.805
Okay. All right.

37:47.015 --> 37:49.433
You're kind of picking your
head up, buddy. Don't do that.

37:50.936 --> 37:52.561
Is this okay?

37:52.729 --> 37:54.563
That's what you wanna wear?

37:55.523 --> 37:56.941
That's okay with me then.

37:57.150 --> 37:59.652
Good luck walking down
the street, that's all I can say.

38:01.363 --> 38:03.072
Way to block it.
Now stay with it.

38:03.239 --> 38:05.449
You're the next Willie Randolph.
Remember that.

38:06.576 --> 38:08.577
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

38:15.460 --> 38:18.337
There was this guy
Chief Jay Strongbow who
used to do a sleeper hold.

38:18.546 --> 38:19.755
Put your arm
under here.

38:19.965 --> 38:22.883
Lift this arm, okay?
Slide under and try
to lock wrists, okay?

38:23.051 --> 38:26.095
Lock wrists. You're gonna...
Let me show you. Watch.

38:26.346 --> 38:29.556
Throw him into the ropes
and he comes back and boom!

38:29.724 --> 38:32.059
Get him. Get him.
Lock him up. Lock him up.

38:32.268 --> 38:33.894
Lock wrists. Okay?

38:34.062 --> 38:35.938
You bring him down slow. Slow.

38:36.106 --> 38:37.564
Apply pressure.

38:37.774 --> 38:39.400
And he's going to sleep
right now.

38:42.237 --> 38:44.071
See, he's out.

38:46.574 --> 38:50.285
Nazo.

38:54.499 --> 38:55.624
Wake up.

39:01.631 --> 39:04.591
SONNY:
You'll be the only kid your age
with a slingshot, I promise.

39:05.051 --> 39:08.429
Go have some fun.
Shoot a few beer cans or
something like that, all right?

39:12.142 --> 39:13.434
You like that?

39:18.523 --> 39:19.982
Sonny, Sonny, come here!

39:20.150 --> 39:22.151
What is it? What's the matter?

39:28.074 --> 39:29.658
Let me have that.

39:30.744 --> 39:33.662
Go to your room. I think.
Or do whatever you want.

39:34.664 --> 39:36.832
It's gonna be fun. You nervous?

39:37.042 --> 39:39.293
No? You're excited, aren't you?

39:39.544 --> 39:42.296
Let's go. Up, up, up.

39:42.464 --> 39:45.549
Okay. Here comes some candy.

39:48.303 --> 39:50.137
Hey, how you doing?

39:50.638 --> 39:53.015
Happy Halloween!
We got a first-timer out here.

39:53.183 --> 39:55.309
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

39:57.645 --> 39:59.063
Do the right thing, buddy.

39:59.272 --> 40:01.440
We want some candy!

40:05.945 --> 40:08.447
Hang on right here for a second,
all right? Don't move.

40:13.495 --> 40:15.162
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

40:23.171 --> 40:24.671
Yeah, that's it.

40:26.091 --> 40:28.008
Yeah, CDs. You like that?

40:28.468 --> 40:31.887
Yeah. He's not happy.
What else you got?

40:34.099 --> 40:36.100
Okay, yeah, that's good.
Trick-or-treat.

40:38.394 --> 40:40.395
Say, "Happy Halloween."
Happy Halloween.

40:40.647 --> 40:42.648
Thank you.

40:42.899 --> 40:45.400
Next year,
be prepared, moron.

40:48.738 --> 40:50.364
What's with the kid
wearing a cummerbund?

40:50.615 --> 40:52.366
I let him wear whatever
he wants to wear.

40:52.617 --> 40:54.076
Those boots
are the best.
Whose are they?

40:54.244 --> 40:56.120
I know, right?
I think they're Kevin's.

40:56.412 --> 40:59.706
I'll have a hot dog with
the mustard and a knish.

40:59.874 --> 41:01.416
Frankenstein,
what do you want?

41:01.668 --> 41:03.127
Thirty packets of ketchup.

41:03.336 --> 41:05.712
All right. Thirty packets
of ketchup.

41:06.214 --> 41:07.256
Ow! Hey.

41:07.423 --> 41:08.632
SONNY:
Nice cut, pal.

41:10.718 --> 41:11.718
SONNY:
Frankenstein.

41:12.137 --> 41:14.221
Do that thing I taught you
the other day.

41:14.389 --> 41:15.597
[HAWKS]

41:20.436 --> 41:21.520
That's cool.

41:21.688 --> 41:24.439
It took him like 20 minutes
to learn that, man.
He's quick. He's smart.

41:24.649 --> 41:26.692
TOMMY: And he loves ketchup.
Yeah, he does.

41:26.901 --> 41:29.278
This is like a whole
new school of child
raising I'm doing.

41:29.529 --> 41:31.363
You give the kid options
instead of orders.

41:31.531 --> 41:32.906
You know, let him make
the right decision.

41:33.074 --> 41:34.366
You're a pioneer.
Thanks.

41:34.534 --> 41:36.410
So you two just chill out
together all day?

41:36.578 --> 41:38.579
Basically. Went to
the park yesterday.

41:38.746 --> 41:41.123
Hung out on the monkey bars.
The kid did eight chin-ups.

41:41.291 --> 41:43.792
Eight? I can't even do one
with these scrawny arms.

41:44.043 --> 41:46.170
They're not scrawny.
They're nice.

41:47.088 --> 41:49.256
So, Julian, what do you
wanna do tomorrow?

41:49.424 --> 41:51.175
I wanna go to school.

41:51.384 --> 41:54.803
Look at that. I don't force him,
he makes the right decision.
Way to go, kid.

41:54.971 --> 41:57.806
We'll enroll you on Monday, all right?
Let's just enjoy the weekend.

41:57.974 --> 41:59.266
Do the thing again.

41:59.434 --> 42:00.851
[HAWKS]

42:06.816 --> 42:09.693
That one touched the ground.
That one touched the ground.

42:09.903 --> 42:10.986
That was awesome!

42:11.237 --> 42:12.571
TOMMY:
Good job.

42:12.947 --> 42:16.074
[WISE GUYS' "OOH LA LA"
PLAYING]

42:16.242 --> 42:19.453
Help me! Help me!
Hey, hey, shh.

42:19.621 --> 42:20.621
Please help me.

42:20.788 --> 42:22.497
I don't know where I live.

42:22.749 --> 42:25.000
This isn't a big problem.
We'll just, um...

42:25.210 --> 42:27.419
We'll find your parents.

42:27.712 --> 42:29.922
What's your name?
Frankenstein.

42:30.131 --> 42:32.132
Frankenstein. Okay.
SONNY: There you are.

42:32.342 --> 42:34.468
There you are.
Are you okay, buddy?

42:35.470 --> 42:37.471
I turned my head for one second
and he disappeared.

42:37.639 --> 42:40.349
Don't you ever do that to me
again, okay? Don't do that.

42:40.934 --> 42:43.644
Thank you so much for being
sweet to my little boy here.

42:43.853 --> 42:46.521
You're welcome, Sonny.
Sonny?

42:46.814 --> 42:49.983
I think my sister, Corinne,
is engaged to your roommate.

42:50.151 --> 42:52.986
Your sister's Corinne?
That sucks.

42:53.154 --> 42:55.989
Yeah, I'm up from D.C.
I was at that party,

42:56.241 --> 42:58.325
the one where we wasted
the good surprise on you.

42:58.493 --> 43:00.118
Oh, yeah.
Sorry about that.

43:00.662 --> 43:02.371
So, what, you have a son now?

43:02.622 --> 43:05.499
I'm not really his dad.
I'm more of a temporary
father-figure type

43:05.750 --> 43:08.543
until Social Services can get
another family for him.

43:08.753 --> 43:10.837
At which point,
you'll have to find a new way

43:11.047 --> 43:13.882
to initiate conversations
with girls in the park.

43:14.133 --> 43:15.842
Yeah, that's correct.
Mm-hm.

43:16.511 --> 43:18.679
Hey! Hey!

43:19.180 --> 43:20.389
Good job, buddy!

43:20.765 --> 43:22.140
He's peeing on his own.

43:22.350 --> 43:23.976
Keep it flowing! That's it!

43:24.185 --> 43:26.270
Go! Go!

43:26.688 --> 43:29.273
So, um, does Corinne's
sister have a name?

43:29.774 --> 43:31.358
It's Layla.
Layla?

43:31.526 --> 43:33.402
Mm-hm.
I like your song.

43:34.362 --> 43:35.654
Could you do me
a big favor?

43:35.863 --> 43:37.281
Could you just hang out
with me tonight?

43:37.448 --> 43:40.200
I don't want the kid to think
he's a failure because he
couldn't get me a date.

43:40.368 --> 43:42.577
I really can't.
No?

43:42.745 --> 43:44.579
No, I just have a ton
of work to do.

43:44.789 --> 43:46.915
I see. Hang on a second.

43:47.083 --> 43:48.292
Come here.

43:49.210 --> 43:50.794
[WHISPERING]

43:52.380 --> 43:56.508
Layla, if you don't come over
to Sonny's apartment tonight,

43:56.718 --> 43:59.511
there's a good chance
that I'll develop a stutter.

44:01.014 --> 44:04.099
P-P-P-Please
don't do this to me.

44:04.726 --> 44:07.102
That is so cheap.
What?

44:07.312 --> 44:11.315
[YVONNE ELLIMAN'S
"IF I CAN'T HAVE YOU"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

44:14.360 --> 44:16.570
So I'm working
in a tollbooth now.

44:16.738 --> 44:19.114
I originally wanted to be
a male model,

44:19.365 --> 44:22.576
but turns out I'm not
very good-looking,
so that didn't work out.

44:22.744 --> 44:24.244
I'm sorry
to hear that.

44:24.454 --> 44:26.204
I'm all right.
I'm recovering.

44:26.414 --> 44:29.124
This is my favorite part
of the song right here.

44:29.375 --> 44:31.376
[SINGS]

44:32.587 --> 44:34.755
Better keep it down low.
The kid's gonna wake up.

44:34.922 --> 44:36.798
JULIAN:
Sonny!

44:36.966 --> 44:38.467
Too late.

44:38.634 --> 44:40.761
Okay. Just hang out
a little bit, all right?

44:40.928 --> 44:43.722
I'll be right back.
Don't go sneaking out.

44:45.475 --> 44:48.769
What are you doing?
You forgot to say good night.

44:48.936 --> 44:50.103
What do you mean? I did?

44:50.355 --> 44:52.939
I can't go to sleep
until you say good night.

44:53.149 --> 44:55.776
I didn't know that.
I'm sorry. Good night.

44:56.277 --> 44:57.944
Go to sleep now,
all right?

44:58.112 --> 44:59.613
What'd we learn
about girls today?

44:59.781 --> 45:03.325
Initiating the conversation
is half the battle.

45:03.493 --> 45:05.786
Bingo. Now sleep, okay?

45:06.662 --> 45:08.955
[SONNY SNORING]

45:09.123 --> 45:12.125
[STYX'S "BABE"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

45:13.169 --> 45:16.380
I gave him NyQuil.
He should be out for the night.

45:16.798 --> 45:18.632
This is Styx.
Yeah.

45:18.800 --> 45:21.134
They've been my favorite
band since I was like 12.

45:21.302 --> 45:22.469
You're kidding me.

45:22.637 --> 45:25.389
No, no, I can't help it.
I just love them.

45:25.598 --> 45:27.391
My friends make fun
of me all the time.

45:27.683 --> 45:29.476
My friends make fun
of me all the time too.

45:29.644 --> 45:31.103
I've seen them like 25 times.

45:31.312 --> 45:34.856
Tommy Shaw, when I was 16
years old, I was at the concert,
and he actually reached down,

45:35.024 --> 45:36.650
grabbed my hand,
pulled me on stage.

45:36.818 --> 45:39.152
I got to do the robot voice
for "Mr. Roboto."

45:39.320 --> 45:42.030
Really?
No, I made that up. I'm sorry.

45:42.198 --> 45:44.032
That would've been cool, right?
Yeah.

45:44.325 --> 45:46.201
But seriously though,
my cousin's friends
with their drummer,

45:46.411 --> 45:48.870
so when they come to town,
we get to go out to dinner with them,

45:49.038 --> 45:51.289
and they tell us stories
from the road, stuff like that.

45:51.499 --> 45:53.917
Really?
No, I made that up again too.

45:54.085 --> 45:55.836
I'm sorry.
Okay.

45:56.212 --> 45:59.798
You're not attracted to, like,
60-year-old guys, are you?

45:59.966 --> 46:03.552
No.
Yeah, I don't like them either.

46:03.845 --> 46:05.220
[MUSIC STOPS]

46:05.847 --> 46:07.931
I can't sleep.

46:09.058 --> 46:10.684
Okay.

46:11.227 --> 46:12.519
He can't sleep.

46:12.728 --> 46:16.815
So the rabbit ran
across the street

46:17.024 --> 46:20.152
because he thought
he saw some carrots.

46:20.361 --> 46:22.571
But when he got
across the street,

46:22.822 --> 46:25.740
it turned out they
weren't carrots,
they were peanuts.

46:25.992 --> 46:28.827
Peanuts?
Yeah.

46:29.036 --> 46:31.830
The peanuts belonged
to a squirrel

46:32.039 --> 46:34.875
who had taken them home
from a baseball game.

46:35.042 --> 46:38.336
Right. And then the rabbit
thought to himself,

46:38.754 --> 46:40.839
"Carrots, peanuts,
what's the difference?"

46:41.466 --> 46:44.384
So he asked the squirrel
if he could have some.

46:44.594 --> 46:46.595
And the squirrel said,
"Of course."

46:46.846 --> 46:50.891
And the rabbit was very happy
to make such a nice new friend.

46:52.977 --> 46:54.936
And so was the squirrel.

46:55.104 --> 46:57.898
And the rabbit thought that
the squirrel had very pretty hair.

46:58.608 --> 47:01.067
And nice eyes also.

47:01.986 --> 47:05.113
And the squirrel thought
the rabbit was really nice too.

47:05.490 --> 47:09.075
And then, uh, the rabbit
worked up his courage

47:09.243 --> 47:11.495
and asked the squirrel
if he could have

47:11.746 --> 47:14.498
just the littlest squirrel kiss.

47:15.291 --> 47:19.127
And the squirrel thought
it's just not the right time

47:19.295 --> 47:22.422
in her busy squirrel life
to be kissing any rabbits,

47:22.632 --> 47:26.092
even though this particular rabbit
was very sweet.

47:26.636 --> 47:28.929
And the rabbit got shut down,
did he?

47:31.265 --> 47:35.477
That's all right.
But he was still
thinking maybe

47:35.645 --> 47:38.563
Scuba Steve could get
a squirrel kiss just, you know,

47:38.773 --> 47:40.815
so somebody's getting
some action around here.

47:40.983 --> 47:42.984
[♪♪♪]

47:47.782 --> 47:49.824
Good night, Scuba Steve.

47:50.618 --> 47:52.160
Good night, Frankenstein.

47:54.121 --> 47:55.413
Good night, Sonny.

47:55.623 --> 47:57.290
Good night, Layla.

47:57.458 --> 47:59.459
[♪♪♪]

48:00.461 --> 48:02.337
SONNY:
Don't get caught under
the bleachers with any girls.

48:02.588 --> 48:04.631
It's your first day. Take it slow.

48:04.840 --> 48:07.801
I'll meet you right after school
at 2:30, right out front.

48:08.010 --> 48:09.594
Okay?
You're not staying?

48:09.804 --> 48:12.305
No, I can't stay. I gotta go
get you some more ketchup.

48:12.557 --> 48:14.140
I don't like these kids.

48:14.350 --> 48:17.352
I don't like these kids much either,
but don't you think we should give
them a chance?

48:18.688 --> 48:19.854
No?

48:20.022 --> 48:21.314
All right. How's this?

48:21.482 --> 48:22.649
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

48:22.817 --> 48:23.858
TEACHER:
Okay, everybody. Come on in.

48:24.026 --> 48:25.986
Here are the magic sunglasses.

48:26.195 --> 48:29.072
You put them on
if you feel scared, okay?

48:31.075 --> 48:32.200
Uh-oh! I lost you.

48:32.368 --> 48:34.703
Julian, I don't know where
you are, pal. I'm sorry.

48:34.870 --> 48:37.330
Julian? Yo!
Oh, there you go.

48:38.791 --> 48:41.084
Come on, you go inside
and make some friends.

48:42.086 --> 48:43.878
Oh, yeah, that's a good hug.

48:44.088 --> 48:46.881
All right. Go, go. Go inside.
I'm gonna miss you.

48:50.469 --> 48:52.387
Hi, I like your hat.

48:52.638 --> 48:54.180
What's your name?

48:54.432 --> 48:56.433
[♪♪♪]

49:03.649 --> 49:05.609
[PHONE RINGS]

49:06.027 --> 49:07.694
DAVID LEE ROTH: Might as well...
SONNY: Leave a message!

49:07.862 --> 49:09.863
[VAN HALEN'S "JUMP"
PLAYING ON MESSAGE]

49:10.031 --> 49:12.157
Might as well...
Leave a message!

49:12.366 --> 49:15.368
BROOKS:
Mr. Gerrity, this is Arthur Brooks
from Social Services.

49:15.536 --> 49:16.870
I got good news.

49:17.121 --> 49:19.331
I think we may have found
a family for Julian.

49:19.540 --> 49:24.669
Uh, why don't you give me
a call back as soon as possible
so we can set up a meeting? Bye.

49:25.630 --> 49:27.005
[MACHINE BEEPS]

49:31.218 --> 49:33.219
[♪♪♪]

49:34.555 --> 49:35.597
[PHONE RINGS]

49:35.765 --> 49:37.140
Sierra Club Legal Department.

49:37.433 --> 49:39.017
Can I speak to Layla Maloney?

49:39.435 --> 49:41.645
Layla, line four.

49:43.731 --> 49:45.774
Hello?
You're a lawyer?

49:46.150 --> 49:47.609
What are you doing, goofball?

49:47.777 --> 49:51.154
Waiting for Julian to get
out of school so I can have
somebody to play with.

49:51.739 --> 49:53.531
What are you doing?
I'm swamped.

49:53.741 --> 49:55.867
I even gotta do my laundry
on my lunch hour.

49:56.077 --> 49:59.079
I was gonna do
my laundry today too.
Where are you going?

49:59.288 --> 50:02.082
There's a place nearby,
Suds, on Bleecker.

50:02.291 --> 50:05.210
Yeah, I know that place.
Okay, well, maybe I'll see
you there then.

50:05.419 --> 50:07.712
Maybe. I gotta go.

50:09.298 --> 50:12.300
[HARVEY DANGER'S
"SAVE IT FOR LATER" PLAYING]

50:17.932 --> 50:20.642
SONNY:
So I bought tickets off the guy
and the show was the night before.

50:20.810 --> 50:21.935
LAYLA:
Maybe it was a mistake.

50:22.186 --> 50:26.064
That's really nice, Layla,
but I don't think you know
what's going down on the streets.

50:26.440 --> 50:28.233
It's hard to know
what's going down
on the streets

50:28.442 --> 50:31.945
when you're in an office
seven days a week, Mr. Tollbooth.

50:32.113 --> 50:34.447
You're not gonna tell me
to get a real job, are you?

50:34.615 --> 50:36.741
No. You're a big boy.

50:36.951 --> 50:38.952
I think it's cool you only
work one day a week.

50:40.204 --> 50:42.789
Oh, my God. These are
the cutest things I've ever seen.

50:42.957 --> 50:46.710
Yes, I know. I have them
in yellow also. I wear them
when I work out and stuff.

50:48.129 --> 50:51.256
You know, Sonny, I think
it's great what you're doing
with Julian while you got him.

50:51.632 --> 50:52.716
Yeah, well, I got him.

50:52.925 --> 50:54.634
I was reading this article
the other day that was saying

50:54.844 --> 50:58.179
the most important influences
in a kid's life are his friends.

50:58.347 --> 50:59.597
Really? They said that?
Mm-hm.

50:59.807 --> 51:02.434
You just better hope
he's not hanging out with
all those drug dealers

51:02.601 --> 51:04.018
and delinquents in school.

51:06.522 --> 51:07.647
Sonny, I'm kidding.

51:09.150 --> 51:10.150
I know. I know.

51:11.944 --> 51:14.863
Man, this Yoo-Hoo is good.
You know what else is good?

51:15.114 --> 51:16.740
Smoking dope.

51:17.032 --> 51:20.160
I ain't gonna rat you out.
You know, puffing the cheeba.

51:20.327 --> 51:24.164
Go by the seesaw, smoke a J.
You know what I'm talking about?

51:24.749 --> 51:26.166
I have a bellybutton.

51:26.459 --> 51:29.043
You have a bellybutton?
Well, we all have bellybuttons.
You know what?

51:29.253 --> 51:32.380
We all love Yoo-Hoo.
Especially Yoo-Hoo
with a little rum.

51:32.631 --> 51:34.841
What's rum?
You don't know what rum is?

51:35.050 --> 51:36.134
Rumpelstiltskin?

51:36.635 --> 51:38.094
Rumpelstiltskin.

51:38.304 --> 51:40.889
Rumpelstiltskin's a good man.
So are you guys.

51:41.056 --> 51:44.184
Hey. Stay clean.
Stay focused.

51:44.351 --> 51:47.061
Stay strong. Frankenstein,
have fun with your friends.

51:48.689 --> 51:50.565
What are you doing
scratching so much?

51:50.775 --> 51:52.817
I have ecza...

51:53.027 --> 51:54.486
Eczema? Gross.

51:54.695 --> 51:56.362
How do I make it
stop itching?

51:56.572 --> 51:59.032
I don't know.
You scratch it.

51:59.200 --> 52:01.409
Hey! Spaghetti-O's.
Do you like Spaghetti-O's?

52:02.536 --> 52:03.870
Yeah?

52:04.413 --> 52:05.914
Dented cans are half price.

52:06.081 --> 52:09.542
Microsoft went down three points.
We gotta save some money.

52:11.796 --> 52:13.296
Here, give it a shot.

52:14.799 --> 52:16.299
That's it, boy.

52:16.592 --> 52:18.218
Put it in there.
Feels good, huh?

52:18.427 --> 52:21.054
Hi, Sonny.
Hi, Sonny's friend.

52:21.305 --> 52:22.430
His name's Frankenstein.

52:22.890 --> 52:24.557
Hi, Frankenstein.
Remember me?

52:24.809 --> 52:27.560
Help me. I'm lost.
I don't know where I am.

52:27.728 --> 52:29.187
You don't gotta
do that anymore.

52:29.396 --> 52:31.564
Look at that.
You guys wear the same
size T-shirt. That's cool.

52:31.732 --> 52:34.901
Mm-hm. What's this
I hear about you doing
laundry with my sister?

52:35.069 --> 52:36.528
Did she say I was
doing laundry with her?

52:36.695 --> 52:39.531
Because where I come from,
it's called doing the hibbity-dibbity.

52:39.907 --> 52:40.990
Ow!

52:41.242 --> 52:42.575
I got eczema.

52:42.952 --> 52:45.286
Oh, well, then you
shouldn't scratch it.

52:45.454 --> 52:48.206
Don't tell him what to do. He can
scratch if he wants to scratch.

52:48.415 --> 52:50.124
SONNY: Scratch.
Is that better?

52:50.376 --> 52:52.210
Thank you.
You're welcome.

52:52.628 --> 52:53.920
I didn't know you knew
anything about kids.

52:54.088 --> 52:55.421
I thought you were
a foot doctor.

52:55.631 --> 52:57.966
It's not doctor stuff, stupid.
It's common sense.

52:58.133 --> 52:59.759
Scratching spreads rashes.

52:59.969 --> 53:02.262
Oh, so this is something
you learned at Hooters.

53:03.430 --> 53:04.848
Mm-hm.

53:06.892 --> 53:09.394
What the hell is he doing?
He's shopping.

53:09.603 --> 53:12.105
Microsoft went down
three points.

53:12.773 --> 53:15.108
That's real good.
See you later, Frankenstein.

53:15.276 --> 53:18.862
Hey, you stay away from
the frozen-food section.
Your boobs'll harden.

53:19.947 --> 53:22.949
[SINGING "O SOLE MIO"]

53:26.871 --> 53:28.955
Isn't Little Italy the greatest?

53:29.123 --> 53:33.293
Yeah, I like it. Everyone's
always telling me to hang out
in the Village and SoHo.

53:33.460 --> 53:34.502
Oh, that's all right.

53:34.670 --> 53:38.882
But you gotta respect a place
where the fatter you are,
the cooler you are.

53:43.387 --> 53:45.305
Last time I was here,
that guy was with a different girl.

53:45.472 --> 53:46.806
But I guess he ate her
or something.

53:48.809 --> 53:52.353
Hey, I went to Coney Island
today with the little boy.

53:52.521 --> 53:54.689
You gotta take a look at this.

53:54.940 --> 53:56.357
We had a blast together.

53:56.525 --> 53:58.151
Ohh.

53:58.819 --> 54:00.153
He's so happy.

54:00.404 --> 54:01.821
SONNY:
He is such a good boy.

54:02.031 --> 54:05.491
I tell you, if I have a kid
of my own someday, I hope
he's half as cool as that kid.

54:06.160 --> 54:07.493
Is he picking your nose?

54:07.912 --> 54:10.038
Yeah, he was picking
his own all day,

54:10.289 --> 54:12.624
so I figured he could borrow mine.
That's sweet.

54:13.042 --> 54:15.418
He must be miserable
without you right now.

54:15.711 --> 54:17.211
No, he's in good hands.

54:17.379 --> 54:18.671
Uh, you, sir...

54:19.006 --> 54:21.925
Ooh, look at Brad's body.
Not an ounce of fat on it.

54:22.134 --> 54:24.886
What?
Don't worry. I like yours better.

54:25.054 --> 54:27.013
[MUTTERING]

54:27.389 --> 54:30.350
Okay, I got two queens,
two jacks and an ace.

54:30.559 --> 54:32.226
I win.
Why do you win?

54:32.436 --> 54:36.356
I got a two, a four, a 10,
an eight and a six.

54:36.523 --> 54:37.523
I don't understand.

54:37.691 --> 54:39.359
Why do you win?
Because I win.

54:39.526 --> 54:41.319
What's the name of that game?
I win.

54:41.487 --> 54:42.528
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

54:42.696 --> 54:43.863
I'll get it!

54:45.741 --> 54:48.034
What's up?
Hi, I'm looking for Kevin Gerrity.

54:48.202 --> 54:49.994
Oh, he's in China.
Who are you?

54:50.204 --> 54:53.748
Arthur Brooks, New York City
Social Services. I'm confused.

54:53.999 --> 54:56.542
Chinatown. He loves
those egg rolls.

54:56.961 --> 55:00.880
Well, I've tried contacting
him several times and he
hasn't responded.

55:01.090 --> 55:02.423
I'm concerned.

55:02.591 --> 55:04.384
MIKE:
Hey! Lx-nay on the ketchup-nay.

55:04.593 --> 55:06.552
Have him call me.
All right.

55:07.888 --> 55:09.889
My body's definitely
better than his.

55:10.057 --> 55:11.975
Without question.

55:16.230 --> 55:20.066
So it took you a long time
to pencil me in, Layla.
You work all the time.

55:20.234 --> 55:21.442
I know. I'm really excited.

55:21.610 --> 55:24.237
You're excited about that.
How long you been this crazy?

55:25.864 --> 55:28.449
I guess ever since
I was a little girl.

55:29.368 --> 55:33.621
See, my mom got married
really young and pretty much
just raised us kids.

55:34.081 --> 55:35.790
So when my dad took off,

55:36.041 --> 55:38.584
she wasn't left
with a lot of options.

55:38.752 --> 55:41.796
And I think that's
when I decided

55:42.006 --> 55:44.590
that I just never wanted
to end up in that situation.

55:45.259 --> 55:47.802
Now, that's actually
a good reason to be working.

55:48.053 --> 55:51.806
I guess I feel like I gotta kick ass
while there's ass to be kicked.

55:52.057 --> 55:56.269
Well, you kick that ass
during the day, but at night
you have fun with Sonny.

55:57.271 --> 56:01.524
[SINGING]
The best of times

56:02.818 --> 56:07.030
Are when I'm alone with you

56:09.616 --> 56:13.453
Some rain, some shine

56:19.168 --> 56:21.294
[STYX'S "THE BEST OF TIMES"
PLAYING]

56:21.462 --> 56:25.048
So two guys you were best
friends with in law school
fell in love with each other?

56:25.215 --> 56:27.633
Yeah.
Is that strange for you?

56:27.843 --> 56:29.844
No. I mean,
nothing changed, really.

56:30.054 --> 56:32.305
They watch a different kind
of porno now. But that's it.

56:32.473 --> 56:33.514
[CAR HORN HONKS]

56:33.682 --> 56:35.183
Hello.

56:35.976 --> 56:37.977
SONNY:
My God! This is Corinne's place?

56:38.187 --> 56:40.813
If the girls at Hooters
could see her now.

56:40.981 --> 56:45.151
Do you want your ass kicked?
I'm just kidding around, Layla.

56:46.320 --> 56:48.071
So, um...

56:49.490 --> 56:53.076
I know you're afraid to
get involved and I know
you got a lot of work,

56:53.619 --> 56:57.663
but when I'm not with you,
I'm thinking about you all the time.
Do you have that going on at all?

56:58.082 --> 56:59.123
Maybe.

56:59.333 --> 57:01.834
Maybe we should try
a kiss out. Just...

57:02.086 --> 57:06.339
We owe it to ourselves to see if
we should move to the next level,
see if any sparks fly.

57:07.216 --> 57:08.716
I'm not sure.

57:08.884 --> 57:12.011
I'm not sure either. It's just
that you kissed Scuba Steve.

57:12.179 --> 57:14.847
Ever since then,
he's been strutting around
the apartment bragging,

57:15.099 --> 57:19.310
"I got a kiss the first night.
You've been with her three times,
you got nothing."

57:19.520 --> 57:20.853
Oh, he said that?
Come on.

57:21.021 --> 57:24.357
Let's just give it a shot
just so I can have some
dignity at home.

57:24.608 --> 57:25.900
All right?

57:26.693 --> 57:29.862
Okay.

57:33.117 --> 57:35.076
CORINNE:
Oh, my God!

57:35.244 --> 57:36.702
Gross!

57:36.870 --> 57:38.371
Did I just witness
the first kiss?

57:38.539 --> 57:41.165
Yeah, you did, Corinne.
Thanks a lot for showing up.

57:41.375 --> 57:44.877
Aww, Layla, you didn't actually
enjoy that, did you?

57:45.045 --> 57:47.588
I don't know.
I'm going upstairs.

57:47.756 --> 57:50.007
Wash your mouth out.
He's dirty.

57:50.217 --> 57:51.843
And he's poor.

57:52.052 --> 57:56.055
Hey, what do you got in the bag,
Corinne? Some chicken wings?
Booby tassels?

57:56.348 --> 57:57.390
Shut up.

57:57.558 --> 57:59.058
You have a good sleep
tonight there, Corinne.

57:59.226 --> 58:00.852
Pleasant Hooters.

58:01.895 --> 58:03.896
[♪♪♪]

58:05.399 --> 58:07.233
Come on, come on!
Okay.

58:07.568 --> 58:09.443
This is where
we hang our jackets.

58:09.653 --> 58:10.903
This is my hook.
Good one.

58:11.071 --> 58:12.405
And that's a capertillar.

58:12.656 --> 58:13.865
A caterpillar.

58:14.074 --> 58:16.534
That's right, a capertillar.
Capertillar, all right.

58:16.702 --> 58:19.287
Hey. Staying clean, pal?
Yes.

58:19.538 --> 58:22.331
That's right. You drink the booze,
you lose. Remember that, punk.

58:22.499 --> 58:23.916
Hi.
Hi.

58:24.084 --> 58:26.878
I'm Julian's teacher,
Ms. Foote. You his father?

58:27.045 --> 58:28.588
Yeah, how you doing?
I'm Kevin Gerrity.

58:28.755 --> 58:30.256
I wonder if you'd give me
a few minutes

58:30.424 --> 58:32.592
to go over a couple of things
that have been bothering me.

58:33.051 --> 58:34.093
Sure.

58:34.261 --> 58:36.179
Go take a walk, pal.

58:36.430 --> 58:39.432
Uh, Julian has been displaying
some odd behavior.

58:39.600 --> 58:42.935
Last week he spilled a tube of glue
on the floor and didn't tell anybody.

58:43.103 --> 58:45.438
He just covered it with newspaper.
Uh-huh.

58:45.606 --> 58:49.317
And then one of our students wore
Rollerblades for show-and-tell.

58:49.484 --> 58:52.695
Yeah?
And Julian tripped him with a stick.

58:52.946 --> 58:54.113
I've never...

58:56.783 --> 58:58.659
Julian found it hilarious.

58:58.827 --> 59:01.245
I like him to feel like he can
express himself freely.

59:01.455 --> 59:04.373
I've really never seen
any problems with that.

59:04.541 --> 59:05.917
Eww!

59:08.295 --> 59:11.505
Your boy's making the least
progress of any of the children
in the class.

59:12.132 --> 59:15.843
And frankly, his personal hygiene
is becoming a cause for concern.

59:16.303 --> 59:19.722
He's the smelly kid in class?
I let him become the smelly kid
in class?

59:19.932 --> 59:21.140
What the hell's the matter
with me?

59:21.350 --> 59:23.309
Oh, yes. I've had some
smelly ones before.

59:23.518 --> 59:25.978
But your son is by far the smelliest.

59:26.230 --> 59:28.981
All right, I got you, ma'am.
Take it easy. What do you
think I should do?

59:29.233 --> 59:31.859
Well, you might start by paying
more attention to his schoolwork.

59:32.069 --> 59:33.152
Okay.

59:33.320 --> 59:35.947
The class is giving a presentation of
the Founding Fathers in two weeks.

59:36.156 --> 59:40.326
And Julian has drawn
the part of Benjamin Franklin,
a very important role.

59:40.494 --> 59:41.786
You should do
what you can to help.

59:41.995 --> 59:44.747
All right, all right. I will turn this
all around. That's a promise.

59:44.957 --> 59:46.332
Thank you
very much.

59:46.541 --> 59:49.043
Hey, Stinky, let's get going.
You got us in trouble.

59:49.253 --> 59:50.544
Did he call him
"Stinky"?

59:54.007 --> 59:56.676
Wow, I didn't know this
about George Washington.

59:56.843 --> 59:59.303
Yes, his teeth were
made of wool.

59:59.513 --> 01:00:01.055
Wood.

01:00:01.306 --> 01:00:03.808
Oh. I sorry.
I mix up "D" and "L."

01:00:04.017 --> 01:00:05.268
Well, get it right.

01:00:07.020 --> 01:00:08.688
Why don't you turn
that game off, pal?

01:00:08.897 --> 01:00:10.189
I got four guys left.

01:00:10.399 --> 01:00:11.983
Come on.
Let's study a little bit.

01:00:12.192 --> 01:00:13.359
I don't wanna study.

01:00:13.527 --> 01:00:14.568
Give me that.

01:00:15.570 --> 01:00:18.572
You just killed me.
So what? Relax. You'll play later.

01:00:18.782 --> 01:00:20.408
You can't tell me what to do.

01:00:20.659 --> 01:00:22.368
Really? How about
we take a vote?

01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:24.578
Who thinks the kid
should start studying?

01:00:25.914 --> 01:00:29.083
Who doesn't?
Well, you just lost, two to one.

01:00:29.293 --> 01:00:32.586
No, it's a tie.
That guy doesn't count.
He can't even read.

01:00:33.922 --> 01:00:36.048
I know, I know, I know.
He was just joking around.

01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:40.344
Listen, can you
hang out here a little bit?
I gotta go do something.

01:00:40.554 --> 01:00:41.721
No problem.

01:00:41.888 --> 01:00:42.930
["KANGAROO SONG"
PLAYING ON TV]

01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:44.432
KANGAROO [SINGING]:
Would you like

01:00:44.599 --> 01:00:46.392
KANGAROO & JULIAN [SINGING]:

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:48.394
We'll hop, hop, hop, hop

01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:50.313
What do you say?

01:00:50.480 --> 01:00:51.772
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

01:00:51.940 --> 01:00:53.441
Get the door.

01:00:55.360 --> 01:00:58.112
[♪♪♪]

01:01:00.324 --> 01:01:01.907
Hi, Julian. How you doing?

01:01:02.409 --> 01:01:04.285
I'm Scuba Sam.

01:01:04.453 --> 01:01:06.078
Scuba Steve's father.

01:01:06.330 --> 01:01:09.582
You see, my boy
needs to take a bath.

01:01:09.958 --> 01:01:11.459
The only problem is

01:01:11.710 --> 01:01:13.753
he's afraid to bathe alone.

01:01:13.920 --> 01:01:15.546
So I was wondering

01:01:15.756 --> 01:01:19.258
if maybe you could
keep him company in the tub.

01:01:20.093 --> 01:01:24.263
Terrific. And after the bath,
you have to try and study hard.

01:01:24.473 --> 01:01:27.725
Because if you wanna be
a member of the Scuba Squad,

01:01:27.893 --> 01:01:29.268
you have to be smart.

01:01:29.478 --> 01:01:31.604
I could be in
the Scuba Squad?

01:01:31.772 --> 01:01:35.358
Well, sure. All you have to do
is work hard.

01:01:35.567 --> 01:01:38.152
And don't tell a soul
about the Scuba Squad,

01:01:38.362 --> 01:01:40.613
because then everybody's
gonna wanna join.

01:01:40.781 --> 01:01:42.281
And one more thing,

01:01:42.449 --> 01:01:44.784
be nice to the delivery guy,
would you?

01:01:46.286 --> 01:01:48.079
It's not his fault he can't read.

01:01:48.914 --> 01:01:50.581
Take care.

01:01:50.749 --> 01:01:53.417
[♪♪♪]

01:01:54.628 --> 01:01:57.463
SONNY:
Yeah, yeah. He told me
to watch his boat for him.

01:01:57.631 --> 01:02:00.966
Said that he wanted to talk
to you about some secret
mission or something.

01:02:01.593 --> 01:02:03.969
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:05.721
Okay.

01:02:07.140 --> 01:02:09.600
How come I have to wear
a bathing suit?

01:02:09.810 --> 01:02:11.310
I don't know.
I don't know the rules

01:02:11.478 --> 01:02:15.773
with little kids and grownups
and being naked and just sit down.

01:02:18.151 --> 01:02:21.529
The good news is you're starting
not to smell like a foot anymore.

01:02:21.696 --> 01:02:22.988
Hey, I read something
interesting today.

01:02:23.156 --> 01:02:27.701
You know that Benjamin
Franklin invented bifocals?
That's pretty cool, huh?

01:02:27.869 --> 01:02:28.911
What are they?

01:02:29.079 --> 01:02:30.371
I'll show you
in that book I'm reading.

01:02:30.539 --> 01:02:33.249
There's a lot of cool stuff
in there. It might help you out
with your school play.

01:02:33.417 --> 01:02:35.835
Okay.
We'll make this a regular thing.

01:02:36.002 --> 01:02:39.171
Bathing and studying
and eating right.

01:02:39.423 --> 01:02:42.049
Put your head back.
This is what my grandmother
used to do to me.

01:02:42.217 --> 01:02:47.012
"Oh, boy. When I was a little girl,
frankfurters only cost a nickel."

01:02:47.431 --> 01:02:48.514
Can you still have fun?

01:02:48.723 --> 01:02:50.474
Yeah, we can have fun.
But after you study.

01:02:50.684 --> 01:02:53.727
In fact, we gotta get you
dressing differently.

01:02:53.937 --> 01:02:55.354
After you get out,
we'll go to Barney's.

01:02:55.522 --> 01:02:56.564
Barney?

01:02:56.731 --> 01:02:59.358
Not that Barney. A different Barney.
A more expensive Barney.

01:02:59.526 --> 01:03:02.528
[BIG AUDIO DYNAMITE'S "RUSH"
PLAYING]

01:03:08.952 --> 01:03:10.703
All right, one at a time.

01:03:10.954 --> 01:03:12.455
That's one.

01:03:12.622 --> 01:03:13.706
Two.

01:03:13.874 --> 01:03:15.040
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

01:03:15.959 --> 01:03:18.544
SONNY:
See? Urinals are good too.

01:03:27.679 --> 01:03:29.680
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:03:39.274 --> 01:03:40.733
"Electricity."

01:03:40.901 --> 01:03:41.984
Very good.

01:03:42.194 --> 01:03:43.444
"Constitution."

01:03:43.612 --> 01:03:44.862
That's it.

01:03:45.071 --> 01:03:46.280
"Philadelphia."

01:03:46.490 --> 01:03:47.615
Smart. Good.

01:03:50.410 --> 01:03:51.494
"Fish"?

01:03:51.912 --> 01:03:53.245
Yeah.

01:03:53.622 --> 01:03:54.788
"Pony"?
Yes.

01:03:56.750 --> 01:03:57.791
"Hip..."

01:03:58.919 --> 01:04:00.377
"Hiphop..."

01:04:00.545 --> 01:04:01.587
"Hipopynonamous"?

01:04:03.131 --> 01:04:06.008
Damn you! You gave him
the easy ones!

01:04:09.513 --> 01:04:10.930
MAN: Thanks!
You're welcome.

01:04:14.559 --> 01:04:15.601
Slow down.

01:04:16.311 --> 01:04:19.104
You owe me a Sausage McMuffin.
SONNY: Okay.

01:04:20.482 --> 01:04:21.690
[SCREAMS]

01:04:23.068 --> 01:04:24.109
Whoa.

01:04:26.446 --> 01:04:27.530
There's a pole there.

01:04:28.281 --> 01:04:29.949
[SPEAKS GIBBERISH]

01:04:34.663 --> 01:04:36.956
[PIANO PLAYING]

01:04:37.123 --> 01:04:39.166
My name is
Alexander Hamilton.

01:04:39.543 --> 01:04:42.253
I was the first Secretary
of the Treasury.

01:04:42.462 --> 01:04:44.838
I owned a bank
and a newspaper.

01:04:45.131 --> 01:04:47.424
Aaron Bird shot me.

01:04:47.634 --> 01:04:49.635
[LAUGHING AND APPLAUDING]

01:04:51.471 --> 01:04:53.931
Hi, my name is
Benjamin Franklin.

01:04:54.266 --> 01:04:56.809
I was a writer, a diplomat,

01:04:57.102 --> 01:04:59.311
an inventor and a statesman,

01:04:59.646 --> 01:05:03.649
although I only went to school
for two years.

01:05:04.859 --> 01:05:09.196
I wrote many books and invented
many things we still use today.

01:05:11.616 --> 01:05:13.325
All right.

01:05:13.994 --> 01:05:17.663
The Declaration of Independence
is finished.

01:05:19.332 --> 01:05:21.000
Who will be
the first to sign?

01:05:21.209 --> 01:05:24.628
How about you, John Hancock?
KIDS: I want to sign!

01:05:24.796 --> 01:05:26.589
[KIDS CLAMORING]

01:05:28.883 --> 01:05:31.594
Look at my man stand strong.
He's so cute.

01:05:31.761 --> 01:05:33.512
[♪♪♪]

01:05:37.392 --> 01:05:38.642
DELIVERY GUY:
What are your cards?

01:05:38.852 --> 01:05:43.606
I got a six, a five, a jack,
a four and a eight.

01:05:43.815 --> 01:05:44.857
I win.

01:05:45.025 --> 01:05:48.694
What do you mean, you win?
I had a hand just like that
before. I didn't win.

01:05:48.862 --> 01:05:51.322
Because I win.
This is bullshit!

01:05:51.531 --> 01:05:53.198
All right.
Take it easy, man.

01:05:53.366 --> 01:05:55.200
Every time it's different cards.
He still wins.

01:05:55.368 --> 01:05:56.869
So what? Relax. He's a kid.

01:05:57.037 --> 01:06:00.539
There should be same set of rules
for everyone, no matter what age.

01:06:00.749 --> 01:06:02.750
He's gotta learn
how to lose too.

01:06:03.126 --> 01:06:05.586
Hello, Mr. Koufax.
Hey, Mr. Brooks, how you doing?

01:06:05.754 --> 01:06:07.546
I was gonna give you
a buzz.

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:11.258
You just called me Mr. Koufax
though, didn't you?

01:06:11.509 --> 01:06:13.594
It is your name, isn't it?
Sonny Koufax?

01:06:13.762 --> 01:06:16.347
You fraudulently held yourself out
to be Kevin Gerrity

01:06:16.556 --> 01:06:18.557
to gain custody of young
Julian over there.

01:06:18.808 --> 01:06:20.726
Big problem in this state, Sonny.
Well...

01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:22.728
I've delivered
to you before.

01:06:22.896 --> 01:06:25.356
You always order
three pieces of cheesecake.

01:06:26.149 --> 01:06:28.942
The real Kevin Gerrity
called me up, he asked
me to take care of...

01:06:29.152 --> 01:06:30.944
Save it, Mr. Koufax.

01:06:31.196 --> 01:06:33.572
The kid has to come with me now
or I'll have you arrested.

01:06:33.740 --> 01:06:35.074
Take out your
handcuffs then.

01:06:35.241 --> 01:06:38.160
I don't have any handcuffs,
but two policemen downstairs do.

01:06:38.662 --> 01:06:40.913
Listen, Sonny,
I would like to help,

01:06:41.164 --> 01:06:44.917
but my status in your country
is not what you would call legal.

01:06:45.168 --> 01:06:46.251
It's okay.

01:06:46.586 --> 01:06:47.711
I'm Audi.

01:06:47.921 --> 01:06:49.755
Julian, you're gonna
have to come with me.

01:06:49.923 --> 01:06:51.256
Hey, hey, hey.
Just give me...

01:06:51.424 --> 01:06:54.343
Sonny.
One second, pal.

01:06:56.429 --> 01:06:59.807
Would you just please
give me a second to
say goodbye to the kid?

01:07:00.809 --> 01:07:01.850
Take a second.

01:07:06.564 --> 01:07:08.941
[♪♪♪]

01:07:10.193 --> 01:07:12.486
You don't want me here
anymore?

01:07:12.779 --> 01:07:14.655
No, that's not it, pal.

01:07:14.823 --> 01:07:17.157
You just gotta go away
for a little while.

01:07:17.325 --> 01:07:19.827
How long am I going away for?

01:07:19.994 --> 01:07:21.995
I don't wanna lie to you.

01:07:24.332 --> 01:07:26.125
I don't think we're gonna

01:07:26.626 --> 01:07:28.752
be seeing each other
anymore.

01:07:30.213 --> 01:07:33.090
I screwed up, pal.
I'm so sorry.

01:07:34.008 --> 01:07:35.342
Come here.

01:07:36.010 --> 01:07:37.219
Put your coat on.

01:07:42.976 --> 01:07:45.436
It's not your fault, okay?
I'm the idiot.

01:07:45.729 --> 01:07:47.813
I don't wanna go.
I know you don't.

01:07:47.981 --> 01:07:50.441
I know, but you have to,
and you're gonna be okay,
all right?

01:07:53.445 --> 01:07:55.529
Please don't make me go.

01:07:55.739 --> 01:07:58.198
I'm sorry, but I don't know
what else to do.

01:07:58.366 --> 01:08:00.868
I won't play
the kangaroo song anymore.

01:08:01.453 --> 01:08:02.786
Come on.

01:08:02.996 --> 01:08:04.663
Just go.
You gotta go.

01:08:04.873 --> 01:08:05.998
You gotta go.

01:08:07.834 --> 01:08:10.335
JULIAN:
I don't wanna go. I promise,

01:08:10.503 --> 01:08:13.505
I'm sorry. I don't even
like that song anymore.

01:08:13.757 --> 01:08:15.841
I know, pal. That's not it.

01:08:16.009 --> 01:08:19.178
But I wipe my own ass!
I wipe my own ass!

01:08:20.680 --> 01:08:22.346
I know.

01:08:41.533 --> 01:08:43.911
Layla, they took the kid.
Who?

01:08:44.078 --> 01:08:46.580
Social Services.
I gotta get him back.

01:08:46.831 --> 01:08:48.707
What do you mean?
You said this was
just temporary.

01:08:48.875 --> 01:08:51.835
I know, I know. I can't
have it be temporary.
It's gotta be permanent.

01:08:52.045 --> 01:08:53.712
Okay, what can we do?

01:08:53.921 --> 01:08:57.341
Well, I filed a brief to get
custody based on the
best interests of the child.

01:08:57.550 --> 01:09:01.386
And Tommy knew one of the clerks,
so they fast-tracked the hearing.
It's Tuesday. You gotta be there.

01:09:01.554 --> 01:09:03.388
This Tuesday?
What, you got work?

01:09:03.598 --> 01:09:06.600
I gotta go to Washington.
There's a hearing to dismiss
my case.

01:09:06.850 --> 01:09:08.393
Well, can you get
somebody else to do it?

01:09:08.603 --> 01:09:11.104
I'm sorry, Sonny.
I can't. It's my case.

01:09:11.314 --> 01:09:14.441
What about Julian's case?
We don't even know where
this kid's gonna end up.

01:09:14.734 --> 01:09:18.237
Sonny, this is exactly why
I didn't wanna get involved.

01:09:18.446 --> 01:09:20.404
I had things going
just the way I wanted.

01:09:20.615 --> 01:09:24.493
And then I'm sitting at the park,
and you and this kid just come
barging into my life,

01:09:24.702 --> 01:09:27.703
and it's screwing up everything
I had planned.

01:09:27.956 --> 01:09:30.916
A kid showed up on my doorstep.
You think I planned on that?

01:09:31.125 --> 01:09:32.709
But I fell in love with him.

01:09:34.045 --> 01:09:36.046
So now my plans have changed.

01:09:37.924 --> 01:09:41.218
[SHERYL CROW'S
"SWEET CHILD O' MINE" PLAYING]

01:10:31.102 --> 01:10:32.519
BAILIFF:
All rise.

01:10:39.694 --> 01:10:40.736
JUDGE:
Good morning.

01:10:40.904 --> 01:10:43.780
We're here to determine
proper custody of Julian McGrath,

01:10:43.990 --> 01:10:47.200
also known as Julian Gerrity,
a minor child.

01:10:47.410 --> 01:10:48.994
Representing the city
of New York?

01:10:49.162 --> 01:10:50.537
Ted Castellucci.

01:10:50.788 --> 01:10:52.664
Arthur Brooks,
Social Services.

01:10:52.832 --> 01:10:54.833
And representing
Sonny Koufax?

01:10:55.001 --> 01:10:56.168
Phillip D'Amato.

01:10:56.336 --> 01:10:57.419
Thomas Grayton.

01:10:57.712 --> 01:11:00.297
Plus, I'll pretty much
be representing myself,
Your Honor.

01:11:00.506 --> 01:11:01.548
Anyone else?

01:11:01.716 --> 01:11:04.009
Layla Maloney,
Your Honor.

01:11:06.846 --> 01:11:07.888
Thank you.

01:11:08.056 --> 01:11:09.640
Does this mean that
you love me, Layla?

01:11:09.849 --> 01:11:11.433
Something like that.

01:11:12.226 --> 01:11:13.727
JUDGE:
First witness.

01:11:13.937 --> 01:11:16.688
Koufax is a good egg.
He was nice to that kid.

01:11:17.440 --> 01:11:20.692
But he fights like a girl.
You like that?

01:11:20.944 --> 01:11:22.694
I'm right here, miss.

01:11:22.862 --> 01:11:24.154
What are you
gonna do about it?

01:11:24.322 --> 01:11:25.572
[LAUGHING]

01:11:26.532 --> 01:11:28.241
What, are you drunk,
Mr. Herlihy?

01:11:28.451 --> 01:11:31.203
Well, I had a few chardonnays.
What of it?

01:11:32.038 --> 01:11:33.246
Get off the stand, please.

01:11:33.706 --> 01:11:35.040
You got it.

01:11:35.541 --> 01:11:37.084
I've got a few problems.

01:11:37.502 --> 01:11:38.752
Off to a good start.

01:11:39.003 --> 01:11:43.840
Mr. Koufax is a really cool guy.
I wish my dad was as cool as him.

01:11:44.050 --> 01:11:45.759
You see, my dad
was a military man.

01:11:46.552 --> 01:11:49.554
Guess I wasn't such
a "good soldier."

01:11:49.973 --> 01:11:54.768
When I was 35 years old,
he attempted to give me a crew cut
while I was sleeping one afternoon.

01:11:55.061 --> 01:11:57.562
I woke up, broke his arm,
haven't seen him since.

01:11:58.106 --> 01:12:01.024
I'd rather live out on the streets
than under his freaky-ass rules.

01:12:06.698 --> 01:12:11.994
Ah, anyway, I think
Mr. Koufax should be
acquitted of all the charges.

01:12:13.246 --> 01:12:17.124
If O.J. Can get away with murder,
why can't Sonny have his kid?

01:12:18.584 --> 01:12:19.918
This guy knows
what I'm talking about.

01:12:20.086 --> 01:12:22.087
[CROWD CHUCKLING]

01:12:22.922 --> 01:12:24.631
No more questions.

01:12:26.134 --> 01:12:27.968
No more questions...

01:12:28.261 --> 01:12:30.887
And how long have
you been delivering
food to Mr. Koufax?

01:12:31.097 --> 01:12:32.764
I deliver food
for six years.

01:12:32.932 --> 01:12:36.018
Plus, I'm stripper.
But I've put on weight
so it's problem.

01:12:36.227 --> 01:12:40.313
I see. And in your experience,
was Sonny a good father to Julian?

01:12:40.565 --> 01:12:43.275
Oh, yes. They make terrific pair.

01:12:43.443 --> 01:12:45.861
They went together like
lamb and tuna fish.

01:12:46.029 --> 01:12:47.612
[CROWD MURMURING]

01:12:47.780 --> 01:12:49.322
Lamb and tuna fish?

01:12:49.949 --> 01:12:51.575
Maybe like spaghetti
and meatball?

01:12:51.743 --> 01:12:53.452
You more comfortable
with that analogy?

01:12:53.619 --> 01:12:55.871
HOMELESS GUY:
Yes, considering we're in America.

01:12:56.039 --> 01:12:58.707
I mean, if you don't like
spaghetti and meatballs,
why don't you get the hell out?

01:12:58.875 --> 01:13:00.542
I'll come down there
and give you a crew cut.

01:13:00.793 --> 01:13:02.169
Let's see your clippers.

01:13:02.420 --> 01:13:04.171
Not my problem your
father was sick.

01:13:06.466 --> 01:13:08.008
Stop yelling at me!

01:13:08.176 --> 01:13:09.217
[HOMELESS GUY SCREAMS]

01:13:09.385 --> 01:13:10.719
[LAUGHING]

01:13:11.179 --> 01:13:13.680
Order! Order! Order!

01:13:13.848 --> 01:13:15.432
Excuse me.
Am I in the right room?

01:13:15.641 --> 01:13:16.808
Who the hell are you?

01:13:17.060 --> 01:13:18.685
I'm Mr. Koufax's co-counsel.

01:13:18.853 --> 01:13:20.645
He has enough co-counsels.

01:13:20.813 --> 01:13:22.481
Well...

01:13:23.775 --> 01:13:24.983
one more wouldn't hurt.

01:13:25.193 --> 01:13:26.651
Let's get on with it.
Next witness.

01:13:26.861 --> 01:13:29.863
Your Honor, Mr. Koufax
is simply parading his
buddies up there.

01:13:30.073 --> 01:13:32.491
Can't they find someone
who isn't a friend?

01:13:32.700 --> 01:13:34.993
PHIL: And what were Julian
and Mr. Koufax doing when
you saw them?

01:13:35.161 --> 01:13:36.203
Shopping.

01:13:36.370 --> 01:13:39.331
And did Mr. Koufax
appear to be an attentive
and loving father?

01:13:39.499 --> 01:13:40.999
He certainly did.

01:13:41.334 --> 01:13:43.543
And how long have you
disliked Mr. Koufax?

01:13:43.711 --> 01:13:45.045
Since the day I met him.

01:13:45.213 --> 01:13:48.340
And for the record,
where did you work while you
attended medical school?

01:13:49.842 --> 01:13:51.218
Hooters.

01:13:53.012 --> 01:13:54.805
No further questions.

01:13:55.723 --> 01:13:57.182
Asshole.

01:13:57.391 --> 01:13:58.725
Next witness.

01:13:59.227 --> 01:14:01.311
Your Honor, we'd like
to call Julian McGrath.

01:14:01.479 --> 01:14:03.438
[♪♪♪]

01:14:15.201 --> 01:14:18.537
If it's okay with you, Julian,
I'd like to ask you a few questions.

01:14:18.871 --> 01:14:20.580
This is just
you and me talking,

01:14:20.748 --> 01:14:22.916
so don't even pay attention
to all these people, okay?

01:14:23.126 --> 01:14:25.210
Can you tell me
how old you are?

01:14:26.921 --> 01:14:28.630
Your Honor, one second.

01:14:31.217 --> 01:14:32.300
[WHISPERS]

01:14:41.727 --> 01:14:43.395
That's better, huh?

01:14:43.729 --> 01:14:45.438
Now can you tell me
how old you are?

01:14:45.773 --> 01:14:47.023
Five.

01:14:47.233 --> 01:14:48.441
And what's your birthday?

01:14:48.609 --> 01:14:50.318
July 15th.

01:14:50.486 --> 01:14:51.778
Do you know where
you were born?

01:14:52.029 --> 01:14:53.071
Toronto.

01:14:53.281 --> 01:14:55.699
Toronto? I thought
you were from Buffalo.

01:14:56.075 --> 01:14:58.743
I moved to Buffalo
with my mommy.

01:14:58.911 --> 01:15:02.080
LAYLA:
And for the past six weeks,
you've been living with Sonny, right?

01:15:02.665 --> 01:15:03.999
Yes.

01:15:04.208 --> 01:15:05.750
Did you and Sonny
have fun together?

01:15:05.918 --> 01:15:06.960
Yes.

01:15:07.128 --> 01:15:08.920
What kind of things
would you do with Sonny?

01:15:09.172 --> 01:15:13.091
He taught me how to do the sleeper
hold like Chief Jay Strongbow.

01:15:13.676 --> 01:15:14.968
LAYLA:
That's nice.

01:15:15.178 --> 01:15:16.219
Anything else?

01:15:16.429 --> 01:15:18.805
He taught me how to pee
on a building.

01:15:19.265 --> 01:15:20.307
LAYLA:
Really?

01:15:23.978 --> 01:15:28.607
And he taught me that Styx
was one of the greatest
American rock bands.

01:15:28.816 --> 01:15:30.609
And they only caught
a bad rap

01:15:30.818 --> 01:15:34.279
because most critics
are cynical assholes.

01:15:34.447 --> 01:15:36.448
[CROWD CHUCKLING]

01:15:36.949 --> 01:15:38.992
Well, I think we'd all
agree with that.

01:15:40.953 --> 01:15:43.163
Now, before you came to Sonny's
apartment, do you remember

01:15:43.331 --> 01:15:45.457
the last thing your mommy
said to you was?

01:15:45.625 --> 01:15:49.252
That she loved me and I was
gonna live with my new daddy.

01:15:49.462 --> 01:15:52.339
And if your mother could
pick anyone in the world
to be your new daddy,

01:15:52.590 --> 01:15:53.840
who do you think she'd pick?

01:15:54.008 --> 01:15:55.717
Sonny.

01:15:56.636 --> 01:15:57.844
LAYLA:
Thank you, Julian.

01:15:58.095 --> 01:15:59.471
You can step down now.

01:15:59.639 --> 01:16:01.640
[♪♪♪]

01:16:04.435 --> 01:16:06.102
That went good though,
don't you think?

01:16:06.354 --> 01:16:09.314
I don't know. Judge
doesn't look too happy.

01:16:09.649 --> 01:16:12.150
Mr. Koufax, anyone else?

01:16:16.948 --> 01:16:19.282
I'd like to call upon myself,
Your Honor.

01:16:19.492 --> 01:16:20.784
Awesome.

01:16:20.993 --> 01:16:23.995
And which of your esteemed
co-counsels will be examining you?

01:16:26.040 --> 01:16:28.375
My father,
Lenny Koufax.

01:16:28.626 --> 01:16:29.793
What?

01:16:30.253 --> 01:16:31.503
Forget it, Sonny.

01:16:31.671 --> 01:16:33.255
What is going on?

01:16:33.464 --> 01:16:34.839
Your Honor, there is
nobody in this world

01:16:35.007 --> 01:16:37.801
who thinks I shouldn't have a child
more than that man back there.

01:16:38.135 --> 01:16:41.680
He also happens to be
one of the most respected
lawyers in all of Florida.

01:16:41.847 --> 01:16:45.976
So I figure if I can make a believer
out of him, I can make a believer
out of everybody in this court.

01:16:46.143 --> 01:16:47.227
Objection,
Your Honor.

01:16:47.395 --> 01:16:50.772
This court is after the truth,
not the opinion of the
defendant's father.

01:16:50.982 --> 01:16:53.358
You want my opinion?
My son is a moron.

01:16:53.526 --> 01:16:55.986
I withdraw my objection.
Please proceed.

01:16:56.153 --> 01:16:57.988
Mr. Koufax.

01:17:00.908 --> 01:17:02.575
This is a big mistake, Sonny.

01:17:03.077 --> 01:17:06.496
The only reason I came today
is to make sure you didn't
end up in jail for this.

01:17:06.706 --> 01:17:08.540
Well, then that was nice
of you. Thank you.

01:17:08.708 --> 01:17:11.584
To do what I think is right here.
Okay.

01:17:11.794 --> 01:17:14.379
After this is over, get your
fingernails cut. They're too long.

01:17:14.547 --> 01:17:15.547
Okay, Dad.

01:17:15.798 --> 01:17:17.173
MR. KOUFAX:
Your Honor, this case is simple.

01:17:18.342 --> 01:17:22.887
It is absurd to think that
Sonny Koufax is ready
to raise a child.

01:17:23.097 --> 01:17:24.848
Objection!
Shut up, Tommy.

01:17:25.433 --> 01:17:26.933
Sorry, Mr. Koufax.

01:17:27.560 --> 01:17:34.107
First of all, how did this
sweet little boy, Julian,
end up under your supervision?

01:17:35.192 --> 01:17:38.445
I told Social Services
that my name was
Kevin Gerrity.

01:17:38.821 --> 01:17:41.072
Of course, you are not Kevin Gerrity.
No.

01:17:41.240 --> 01:17:42.907
So you lied.
Yes.

01:17:43.075 --> 01:17:46.077
MR. KOUFAX:
Like the time I found a bag of pot
in your underwear drawer

01:17:46.329 --> 01:17:49.122
and you told me that you thought
they were pencil shavings.

01:17:49.999 --> 01:17:51.082
Yeah.

01:17:51.584 --> 01:17:54.794
And remember when I called you up
and told you that your Aunt Fay
was coming to New York,

01:17:54.962 --> 01:17:57.213
and I wanted you to take
her around, show her the city?

01:17:57.423 --> 01:17:59.924
And you said that you had
better things to do, didn't you?

01:18:00.134 --> 01:18:01.259
That's right.

01:18:01.469 --> 01:18:05.472
Now, I'm curious.
Just what were those better
things that you had to do?

01:18:07.600 --> 01:18:11.770
Jethro Tull had a reunion concert
in New Jersey, so I caught that.

01:18:11.937 --> 01:18:13.355
MR. KOUFAX:
Uh-huh.

01:18:14.106 --> 01:18:16.274
And what happened to your
Aunt Fay that weekend?

01:18:17.151 --> 01:18:18.234
She died.

01:18:18.402 --> 01:18:19.444
Yes, she did.

01:18:20.905 --> 01:18:23.448
By any chance, did you happen
to make it to her funeral?

01:18:23.824 --> 01:18:24.866
No.

01:18:25.034 --> 01:18:28.286
Why not?
I went to Jones Beach,

01:18:28.454 --> 01:18:30.121
got drunk and fell asleep.

01:18:30.289 --> 01:18:31.289
Hell, yes!

01:18:32.666 --> 01:18:33.958
Some role model.

01:18:34.460 --> 01:18:35.502
Yeah.

01:18:35.753 --> 01:18:37.170
Your Honor,

01:18:37.880 --> 01:18:39.839
my son doesn't have
health insurance.

01:18:40.007 --> 01:18:42.008
He doesn't know
how to boil an egg.

01:18:42.176 --> 01:18:45.887
He filed for social security
at the age of 30.

01:18:46.430 --> 01:18:49.307
He is a drain on the economy,
on the country,

01:18:49.517 --> 01:18:51.351
and most of all, on me!

01:18:53.813 --> 01:18:57.315
Your Honor,
to give this young man

01:18:58.442 --> 01:19:02.320
custody over another life
is not only wrong,

01:19:02.613 --> 01:19:03.822
it's insane.

01:19:07.785 --> 01:19:10.203
[♪♪♪]

01:19:10.413 --> 01:19:12.664
Hey. I love you.

01:19:13.416 --> 01:19:15.667
What?
You don't have to be scared.

01:19:15.835 --> 01:19:16.960
It's all right.

01:19:17.128 --> 01:19:18.545
What are you talking about?
I'm not scared.

01:19:18.754 --> 01:19:21.840
If I get custody of Julian,
I'll be his father forever.

01:19:22.341 --> 01:19:25.969
And that scares you
because you think there's
a good chance I might fail.

01:19:26.137 --> 01:19:30.056
Sonny, it's more than a chance.
It's a certainty.

01:19:30.266 --> 01:19:31.516
You're wrong, Dad.

01:19:31.976 --> 01:19:36.229
You can be scared that
I might get pickpocketed
in a bad neighborhood

01:19:36.439 --> 01:19:38.398
or I might break
my legs skiing.

01:19:38.607 --> 01:19:42.402
But don't be scared about
me being a dad, because
I will not fail at that. I can't.

01:19:42.862 --> 01:19:44.612
I love this kid too much.

01:19:44.864 --> 01:19:47.365
I love him as much
as you love me, Dad.

01:19:47.575 --> 01:19:50.243
And I'm gonna give him advice
and I'm gonna guide him

01:19:50.453 --> 01:19:52.662
and I'm gonna be there for him
whenever he needs me.

01:19:52.955 --> 01:19:55.748
I'll fly to New York to be
at his court case

01:19:55.958 --> 01:19:58.918
even if I disagree with why
he's there in the first place.

01:19:59.378 --> 01:20:02.505
But, Sonny,
you work in a tollbooth.

01:20:02.798 --> 01:20:04.090
Don't be scared about
me making money.

01:20:04.300 --> 01:20:07.594
I am in love with a beautiful girl
who makes plenty of it.

01:20:07.803 --> 01:20:10.138
She'll be my sugar mama.

01:20:11.390 --> 01:20:13.016
Oh, I gotta get me one of those.

01:20:14.143 --> 01:20:17.687
I know this is the right thing
to do, Dad, because I would
die for this kid

01:20:17.897 --> 01:20:20.440
just so he wouldn't have to
feel one ounce of sadness.

01:20:20.649 --> 01:20:25.028
That's why you're here right now,
to protect me, to be scared for me,

01:20:25.321 --> 01:20:27.238
to be a good father.

01:20:28.240 --> 01:20:30.658
And that's exactly
what I'm gonna be.

01:20:30.826 --> 01:20:32.827
[♪♪♪]

01:20:35.206 --> 01:20:36.748
Hello, Dad?

01:20:37.208 --> 01:20:39.584
Yeah, I just
wanted to say I love you.

01:20:39.835 --> 01:20:43.338
Hi, Mom? Could you
put Dad on the phone
for a second?

01:20:43.756 --> 01:20:45.924
[SPEAKING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

01:20:46.550 --> 01:20:48.551
Can I borrow that
when you're done?

01:20:49.345 --> 01:20:50.929
Your Honor,

01:20:52.181 --> 01:20:53.973
my son deserves this kid.

01:20:54.141 --> 01:20:55.975
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

01:21:04.818 --> 01:21:05.944
[GAVEL BANGING]

01:21:06.111 --> 01:21:07.779
I love you too, sir.

01:21:09.740 --> 01:21:11.324
JUDGE:
Mr. Koufax,

01:21:11.825 --> 01:21:14.327
the fact is
you kidnapped this child.

01:21:14.537 --> 01:21:16.412
Not only shouldn't
you get custody,

01:21:16.622 --> 01:21:19.666
but since you obtained the child
by defrauding the state of New York,

01:21:19.917 --> 01:21:21.960
you should be in jail.

01:21:22.294 --> 01:21:24.295
Bailiff, please remand him until
I can figure out the punishment.

01:21:24.463 --> 01:21:25.797
Your Honor, I think...

01:21:25.965 --> 01:21:27.966
Wait. You can't take him away.

01:21:29.677 --> 01:21:31.886
As that boy's father,
I refuse to press charges.

01:21:32.054 --> 01:21:33.304
[CROWD GASPS]

01:21:34.848 --> 01:21:37.517
Oh, God. Corinne, I'm sorry.

01:21:37.685 --> 01:21:40.186
Six years ago, Joe Carter...

01:21:40.354 --> 01:21:41.563
Joe Carter?

01:21:41.772 --> 01:21:44.065
Toronto and the Phillies.
You know, World Series.

01:21:44.483 --> 01:21:46.859
Mitch Williams just...
We flew up for the night.

01:21:48.487 --> 01:21:50.154
There was a girl.

01:21:50.322 --> 01:21:51.322
Oh, God.

01:21:51.490 --> 01:21:53.992
I'm an idiot.
I was so hammered.

01:21:54.159 --> 01:21:55.577
Chicken wings and Molson 3-0.

01:21:55.744 --> 01:21:57.370
You know Canadian beer
is like moonshine.

01:21:57.580 --> 01:21:58.705
Hell, yes.

01:21:58.872 --> 01:22:01.332
Sonny, you remember, right?
It was at that Toronto Hooters.

01:22:01.959 --> 01:22:03.209
Oh, yeah.

01:22:04.003 --> 01:22:05.628
That was before he met
you though, Corinne.

01:22:05.796 --> 01:22:07.839
That Hooters thing,
that's a coincidence.

01:22:08.173 --> 01:22:09.549
I'm sorry, Corinne.

01:22:09.717 --> 01:22:13.720
I know this changes everything,
but I had to do the right thing.

01:22:15.723 --> 01:22:17.181
Mr. Castellucci.

01:22:17.349 --> 01:22:18.850
I, uh...

01:22:19.018 --> 01:22:21.311
Pending a blood test, I...

01:22:21.478 --> 01:22:22.520
Whatever.

01:22:22.688 --> 01:22:27.525
Then the court grants custody
to Kevin Gerrity, pending
the results of a DNA test.

01:22:27.901 --> 01:22:29.861
No!

01:22:30.029 --> 01:22:32.030
[♪♪♪]

01:22:32.406 --> 01:22:35.533
I want you to be my dad, Sonny.

01:22:35.868 --> 01:22:37.869
I know. I do too, pal.

01:22:38.120 --> 01:22:42.206
But I'm not sure that can happen
exactly the way we want it.

01:22:42.416 --> 01:22:45.209
Because it seems you
already have a daddy.

01:22:45.711 --> 01:22:47.754
But I'll tell you what I can do.

01:22:48.047 --> 01:22:51.507
I can be your friend,
no matter what. All right?

01:22:51.717 --> 01:22:53.426
I'll always be your friend.

01:22:53.677 --> 01:22:56.429
I'll always be your family.
I'll always be around.

01:22:56.722 --> 01:22:58.348
I promise.

01:22:58.641 --> 01:23:00.433
SONNY:
The kid's pretty good
at tying his shoes.

01:23:00.684 --> 01:23:02.727
He's not great at it though,
so you gotta work with him.

01:23:02.895 --> 01:23:04.437
KEVIN:
Maybe I'll teach him
the bunny ears thing.

01:23:04.605 --> 01:23:05.688
SONNY:
What's the bunny ears thing?

01:23:05.898 --> 01:23:08.274
You make the bunny ears,
and then you cross
and pull them through.

01:23:08.442 --> 01:23:12.028
I go with this loop, swoop
and pull thing. He likes that.

01:23:12.196 --> 01:23:13.446
I don't know that one.
The bunny...

01:23:13.614 --> 01:23:15.073
Go with the loop,
swoop and pull thing.

01:23:15.282 --> 01:23:17.033
I swear to God
it's working.

01:23:17.284 --> 01:23:18.451
All right.

01:23:19.036 --> 01:23:23.247
You know what?
Go with the bunny ears thing.
You're his dad, right? I'm sorry.

01:23:23.415 --> 01:23:26.084
It's important, when you eat
at my restaurant,

01:23:26.293 --> 01:23:28.461
you never order BLT.

01:23:28.671 --> 01:23:31.297
You must trust me.
Stay away from BLT, okay?

01:23:31.548 --> 01:23:32.632
Hey, guys.

01:23:32.800 --> 01:23:35.426
I'm gonna leave you
with your dad now, Julian.

01:23:35.594 --> 01:23:38.179
He's a good man right here.
I've known him my whole life.

01:23:38.389 --> 01:23:41.265
So you two have fun
and I'll see you in the
morning for breakfast.

01:23:41.475 --> 01:23:42.684
All right?

01:23:42.893 --> 01:23:44.644
Quit scaring the kid
for a minute.

01:23:44.812 --> 01:23:46.104
Who am I scaring?

01:23:46.313 --> 01:23:47.814
Bye, pal.

01:23:50.067 --> 01:23:51.776
Hey, Julian. Um...

01:23:52.695 --> 01:23:54.946
I just got back from China.
Do you know where that is?

01:23:55.280 --> 01:23:57.490
It's in Asia,
which is by Europe.

01:23:57.658 --> 01:23:59.617
Uh, I brought some
cool stuff back.

01:24:00.160 --> 01:24:01.494
Aah!

01:24:04.456 --> 01:24:06.332
Did you move
the bench?

01:24:07.292 --> 01:24:08.418
That's pretty funny, huh?

01:24:09.586 --> 01:24:12.797
You know what I got?
I got some noisemakers.
Check this out.

01:24:13.966 --> 01:24:15.341
Wanna try one?

01:24:21.014 --> 01:24:22.515
Ah, that's my foot!

01:24:23.100 --> 01:24:26.144
[BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN'S
"GROWIN' UP" PLAYING]

01:24:28.313 --> 01:24:29.981
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

01:24:45.664 --> 01:24:46.748
You're nice man.

01:24:46.915 --> 01:24:50.626
Listen, at my place
I've got Spice Channel.
